28 enum ImmediateMode {
29  kArithmeticImm, // 12 bit unsigned immediate shifted left 0 or 12 bits
30  kShift32Imm, // 0 - 31
31  kShift64Imm, // 0 - 63
32  kLogical32Imm,
33  kLogical64Imm,
34  kLoadStoreImm8, // signed 8 bit or 12 bit unsigned scaled by access size
35  kLoadStoreImm16,
36  kLoadStoreImm32,
37  kLoadStoreImm64,
38  kLoadStoreImm128,
39  kConditionalCompareImm,
40  kNoImmediate
41 };
42 
43 // Adds Arm64-specific methods for generating operands.
44 class Arm64OperandGenerator final : public OperandGenerator {
45  public:
46  explicit Arm64OperandGenerator(InstructionSelector* selector)
47  : OperandGenerator(selector) {}
48 
49  InstructionOperand UseOperand(OpIndex node, ImmediateMode mode) {
50  if (CanBeImmediate(node, mode)) {
51  return UseImmediate(node);
52  }
53  return UseRegister(node);
54  }
55 
56  bool IsImmediateZero(OpIndex node) {
57  if (const ConstantOp* constant =
58  selector()->Get(node).TryCast<ConstantOp>()) {
59  if (constant->IsIntegral() && constant->integral() == 0) return true;
60  if (constant->kind == ConstantOp::Kind::kFloat32) {
61  return constant->float32().get_bits() == 0;
62  }
63  if (constant->kind == ConstantOp::Kind::kFloat64) {
64  return constant->float64().get_bits() == 0;
65  }
66  }
67  return false;
68  }
69 
70  // Use the zero register if the node has the immediate value zero, otherwise
71  // assign a register.
72  InstructionOperand UseRegisterOrImmediateZero(OpIndex node) {
73  if (IsImmediateZero(node)) {
74  return UseImmediate(node);
75  }
76  return UseRegister(node);
77  }
78 
79  // Use the zero register if the node has the immediate value zero, otherwise
80  // assign a register, keeping it alive for the whole sequence of continuation
81  // instructions.
82  InstructionOperand UseRegisterAtEndOrImmediateZero(OpIndex node) {
83  if (IsImmediateZero(node)) {
84  return UseImmediate(node);
85  }
86  return this->UseRegisterAtEnd(node);
87  }
88 
89  // Use the provided node if it has the required value, or create a
90  // TempImmediate otherwise.
91  InstructionOperand UseImmediateOrTemp(OpIndex node, int32_t value) {
92  if (selector()->Get(node).Cast<ConstantOp>().signed_integral() == value) {
93  return UseImmediate(node);
94  }
95  return TempImmediate(value);
96  }
97 
98  bool IsIntegerConstant(OpIndex node) const {
99  int64_t unused;
100  return selector()->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(node, &unused);
101  }
102 
103  std::optional<int64_t> GetOptionalIntegerConstant(OpIndex operation) {
104  if (int64_t constant; MatchSignedIntegralConstant(operation, &constant)) {
105  return constant;
106  }
107  return std::nullopt;
108  }
109 
110  bool CanBeImmediate(OpIndex node, ImmediateMode mode) {
111  const ConstantOp* constant = selector()->Get(node).TryCast<ConstantOp>();
112  if (!constant) return false;
113  if (constant->kind == ConstantOp::Kind::kCompressedHeapObject) {
114  if (!COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) return false;
115  // For builtin code we need static roots
116  if (selector()->isolate()->bootstrapper() && !V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL) {
117  return false;
118  }
119  const RootsTable& roots_table = selector()->isolate()->roots_table();
120  RootIndex root_index;
121  Handle<HeapObject> value = constant->handle();
122  if (roots_table.IsRootHandle(value, &root_index)) {
123  if (!RootsTable::IsReadOnly(root_index)) return false;
124  return CanBeImmediate(MacroAssemblerBase::ReadOnlyRootPtr(
125  root_index, selector()->isolate()),
126  mode);
127  }
128  return false;
129  }
130 
131  int64_t value;
132  return selector()->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(node, &value) &&
133  CanBeImmediate(value, mode);
134  }
135 
136  bool CanBeImmediate(int64_t value, ImmediateMode mode) {
137  unsigned ignored;
138  switch (mode) {
139  case kLogical32Imm:
140  // TODO(dcarney): some unencodable values can be handled by
141  // switching instructions.
142  return internal::Assembler::IsImmLogical(
143  static_cast<uint32_t>(value), 32, &ignored, &ignored, &ignored);
144  case kLogical64Imm:
145  return internal::Assembler::IsImmLogical(
146  static_cast<uint64_t>(value), 64, &ignored, &ignored, &ignored);
147  case kArithmeticImm:
148  return internal::Assembler::IsImmAddSub(value);
149  case kLoadStoreImm8:
150  return IsLoadStoreImmediate(value, 0);
151  case kLoadStoreImm16:
152  return IsLoadStoreImmediate(value, 1);
153  case kLoadStoreImm32:
154  return IsLoadStoreImmediate(value, 2);
155  case kLoadStoreImm64:
156  return IsLoadStoreImmediate(value, 3);
157  case kLoadStoreImm128:
158  return IsLoadStoreImmediate(value, 4);
159  case kNoImmediate:
160  return false;
161  case kConditionalCompareImm:
162  return internal::Assembler::IsImmConditionalCompare(value);
163  case kShift32Imm: // Fall through.
164  case kShift64Imm:
165  // Shift operations only observe the bottom 5 or 6 bits of the value.
166  // All possible shifts can be encoded by discarding bits which have no
167  // effect.
168  return true;
169  }
170  return false;
171  }
172 
173  bool CanBeLoadStoreShiftImmediate(OpIndex node, MemoryRepresentation rep) {
174  if (uint64_t constant;
175  selector()->MatchUnsignedIntegralConstant(node, &constant) &&
176  constant == static_cast<uint64_t>(rep.SizeInBytesLog2())) {
177  return true;
178  }
179  return false;
180  }
181 
182  private:
183  bool IsLoadStoreImmediate(int64_t value, unsigned size) {
184  return internal::Assembler::IsImmLSScaled(value, size) ||
185  internal::Assembler::IsImmLSUnscaled(value);
186  }
187 };
188

191 void VisitRR(InstructionSelector* selector, ArchOpcode opcode, OpIndex node) {
192  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
193  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
194  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 1);
195  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(op.input(0)));
196 }
197 
198 void VisitRRR(InstructionSelector* selector, InstructionCode opcode,
199  OpIndex node) {
200  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
201  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
202  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2);
203  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(op.input(0)),
204  g.UseRegister(op.input(1)));
205 }
206 
207 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
208 void VisitRR(InstructionSelector* selector, InstructionCode opcode,
209  OpIndex node) {
210  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
211  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
212  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 1);
213  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(op.input(0)));
214 }
215 
216 void VisitSimdShiftRRR(InstructionSelector* selector, ArchOpcode opcode,
217  OpIndex node, int width) {
218  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
219  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
220  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2);
221 
222  int64_t constant;
223  if (selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(op.input(1), &constant)) {
224  if (constant % width == 0) {
225  selector->EmitIdentity(node);
226  } else {
227  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
228  g.UseRegister(op.input(0)), g.UseImmediate(op.input(1)));
229  }
230  } else {
231  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(op.input(0)),
232  g.UseRegister(op.input(1)));
233  }
234 }
235 
236 void VisitRRI(InstructionSelector* selector, InstructionCode opcode,
237  OpIndex node) {
238  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
239  const Simd128ExtractLaneOp& op = selector->Cast<Simd128ExtractLaneOp>(node);
240  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(op.input()),
241  g.UseImmediate(op.lane));
242 }
243 
244 void VisitRRIR(InstructionSelector* selector, InstructionCode opcode,
245  OpIndex node) {
246  const Simd128ReplaceLaneOp& op = selector->Cast<Simd128ReplaceLaneOp>(node);
247  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
248  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(op.into()),
249  g.UseImmediate(op.lane), g.UseUniqueRegister(op.new_lane()));
250 }
251 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
252 
253 void VisitRRO(InstructionSelector* selector, ArchOpcode opcode, OpIndex node,
254  ImmediateMode operand_mode) {
255  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
256  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
257  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2);
258  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(op.input(0)),
259  g.UseOperand(op.input(1), operand_mode));
260 }
261 
262 struct ExtendingLoadMatcher {
263  ExtendingLoadMatcher(OpIndex node, InstructionSelector* selector)
264  : matches_(false), selector_(selector), immediate_(0) {
265  Initialize(node);
266  }
267 
268  bool Matches() const { return matches_; }
269 
270  OpIndex base() const {
271  DCHECK(Matches());
272  return base_;
273  }
274  int64_t immediate() const {
275  DCHECK(Matches());
276  return immediate_;
277  }
278  ArchOpcode opcode() const {
279  DCHECK(Matches());
280  return opcode_;
281  }
282 
283  private:
284  bool matches_;
285  InstructionSelector* selector_;
286  OpIndex base_{};
287  int64_t immediate_;
288  ArchOpcode opcode_;
289 
290  void Initialize(OpIndex node) {
291  const ShiftOp& shift = selector_->Get(node).template Cast<ShiftOp>();
292  DCHECK(shift.kind == ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightArithmetic ||
293  shift.kind == ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightArithmeticShiftOutZeros);
294  // When loading a 64-bit value and shifting by 32, we should
295  // just load and sign-extend the interesting 4 bytes instead.
296  // This happens, for example, when we're loading and untagging SMIs.
297  const Operation& lhs = selector_->Get(shift.left());
298  int64_t constant_rhs;
299 
300  if (lhs.Is<LoadOp>() &&
301  selector_->MatchIntegralWord64Constant(shift.right(), &constant_rhs) &&
302  constant_rhs == 32 && selector_->CanCover(node, shift.left())) {
303  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector_);
304  const LoadOp& load = lhs.Cast<LoadOp>();
305  base_ = load.base();
306  opcode_ = kArm64Ldrsw;
307  if (load.index().has_value()) {
308  int64_t index_constant;
309  if (selector_->MatchIntegralWord64Constant(load.index().value(),
310  &index_constant)) {
311  DCHECK_EQ(load.element_size_log2, 0);
312  immediate_ = index_constant + 4;
313  matches_ = g.CanBeImmediate(immediate_, kLoadStoreImm32);
314  }
315  } else {
316  immediate_ = load.offset + 4;
317  matches_ = g.CanBeImmediate(immediate_, kLoadStoreImm32);
318  }
319  }
320  }
321 };
322 
323 bool TryMatchExtendingLoad(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node) {
324  ExtendingLoadMatcher m(node, selector);
325  return m.Matches();
326 }
327 
328 bool TryEmitExtendingLoad(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node) {
329  ExtendingLoadMatcher m(node, selector);
330  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
331  if (m.Matches()) {
332  InstructionOperand inputs[2];
333  inputs[0] = g.UseRegister(m.base());
334  InstructionCode opcode =
335  m.opcode() | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRI);
336  DCHECK(is_int32(m.immediate()));
337  inputs[1] = g.TempImmediate(static_cast<int32_t>(m.immediate()));
338  InstructionOperand outputs[] = {g.DefineAsRegister(node)};
339  selector->Emit(opcode, arraysize(outputs), outputs, arraysize(inputs),
340  inputs);
341  return true;
342  }
343  return false;
344 }
345 
346 bool TryMatchAnyShift(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
347  OpIndex input_node, InstructionCode* opcode, bool try_ror,
348  RegisterRepresentation rep) {
349  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
350 
351  if (!selector->CanCover(node, input_node)) return false;
352  if (const ShiftOp* shift = selector->Get(input_node).TryCast<ShiftOp>()) {
353  // Differently to Turbofan, the representation should always match.
354  DCHECK_EQ(shift->rep, rep);
355  if (shift->rep != rep) return false;
356  if (!g.IsIntegerConstant(shift->right())) return false;
357 
358  switch (shift->kind) {
359  case ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftLeft:
360  *opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_LSL_I);
361  return true;
362  case ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightLogical:
363  *opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_LSR_I);
364  return true;
365  case ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightArithmetic:
366  case ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightArithmeticShiftOutZeros:
367  if (rep == WordRepresentation::Word64() &&
368  TryMatchExtendingLoad(selector, input_node)) {
369  return false;
370  }
371  *opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_ASR_I);
372  return true;
373  case ShiftOp::Kind::kRotateRight:
374  if (try_ror) {
375  *opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_ROR_I);
376  return true;
377  }
378  return false;
379  case ShiftOp::Kind::kRotateLeft:
380  return false;
381  }
382  }
383  return false;
384 }
385 
386 bool TryMatchBitwiseAndSmallMask(OperationMatcher& matcher, OpIndex op,
387  OpIndex* left, int32_t* mask) {
388  if (const ChangeOp* change_op =
389  matcher.TryCast<Opmask::kChangeInt32ToInt64>(op)) {
390  return TryMatchBitwiseAndSmallMask(matcher, change_op->input(), left, mask);
391  }
392  if (const WordBinopOp* bitwise_and =
393  matcher.TryCast<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>(op)) {
394  if (matcher.MatchIntegralWord32Constant(bitwise_and->right(), mask) &&
395  (*mask == 0xFF || *mask == 0xFFFF)) {
396  *left = bitwise_and->left();
397  return true;
398  }
399  if (matcher.MatchIntegralWord32Constant(bitwise_and->left(), mask) &&
400  (*mask == 0xFF || *mask == 0xFFFF)) {
401  *left = bitwise_and->right();
402  return true;
403  }
404  }
405  return false;
406 }
407 
408 bool TryMatchSignExtendShift(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex op,
409  OpIndex* left, int32_t* shift_by) {
410  if (const ChangeOp* change_op =
411  selector->TryCast<Opmask::kChangeInt32ToInt64>(op)) {
412  return TryMatchSignExtendShift(selector, change_op->input(), left,
413  shift_by);
414  }
415 
416  if (const ShiftOp* sar =
417  selector->TryCast<Opmask::kWord32ShiftRightArithmetic>(op)) {
418  const Operation& sar_lhs = selector->Get(sar->left());
419  if (sar_lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftLeft>() &&
420  selector->CanCover(op, sar->left())) {
421  const ShiftOp& shl = sar_lhs.Cast<ShiftOp>();
422  int32_t sar_by, shl_by;
423  if (selector->MatchIntegralWord32Constant(sar->right(), &sar_by) &&
424  selector->MatchIntegralWord32Constant(shl.right(), &shl_by) &&
425  sar_by == shl_by && (sar_by == 16 || sar_by == 24)) {
426  *left = shl.left();
427  *shift_by = sar_by;
428  return true;
429  }
430  }
431  }
432  return false;
433 }
434 
435 bool TryMatchAnyExtend(Arm64OperandGenerator* g, InstructionSelector* selector,
436  OpIndex node, OpIndex left_node, OpIndex right_node,
437  InstructionOperand* left_op,
438  InstructionOperand* right_op, InstructionCode* opcode) {
439  if (!selector->CanCover(node, right_node)) return false;
440 
441  const Operation& right = selector->Get(right_node);
442  OpIndex bitwise_and_left;
443  int32_t mask;
444  if (TryMatchBitwiseAndSmallMask(*selector, right_node, &bitwise_and_left,
445  &mask)) {
446  *left_op = g->UseRegister(left_node);
447  *right_op = g->UseRegister(bitwise_and_left);
448  *opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(
449  (mask == 0xFF) ? kMode_Operand2_R_UXTB : kMode_Operand2_R_UXTH);
450  return true;
451  }
452 
453  OpIndex shift_input_left;
454  int32_t shift_by;
455  if (TryMatchSignExtendShift(selector, right_node, &shift_input_left,
456  &shift_by)) {
457  *left_op = g->UseRegister(left_node);
458  *right_op = g->UseRegister(shift_input_left);
459  *opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(
460  (shift_by == 24) ? kMode_Operand2_R_SXTB : kMode_Operand2_R_SXTH);
461  return true;
462  }
463 
464  if (const ChangeOp* change_op =
465  right.TryCast<Opmask::kChangeInt32ToInt64>()) {
466  // Use extended register form.
467  *opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_SXTW);
468  *left_op = g->UseRegister(left_node);
469  *right_op = g->UseRegister(change_op->input());
470  return true;
471  }
472  return false;
473 }
474 
475 bool TryMatchLoadStoreShift(Arm64OperandGenerator* g,
476  InstructionSelector* selector,
477  MemoryRepresentation rep, OpIndex node,
478  OpIndex index, InstructionOperand* index_op,
479  InstructionOperand* shift_immediate_op) {
480  if (!selector->CanCover(node, index)) return false;
481  if (const ChangeOp* change =
482  selector->Get(index).TryCast<Opmask::kChangeUint32ToUint64>();
483  change && selector->CanCover(index, change->input())) {
484  index = change->input();
485  }
486  const ShiftOp* shift = selector->Get(index).TryCast<Opmask::kShiftLeft>();
487  if (shift == nullptr) return false;
488  if (!g->CanBeLoadStoreShiftImmediate(shift->right(), rep)) return false;
489  *index_op = g->UseRegister(shift->left());
490  *shift_immediate_op = g->UseImmediate(shift->right());
491  return true;
492 }
493 
494 // Bitfields describing binary operator properties:
495 // CanCommuteField is true if we can switch the two operands, potentially
496 // requiring commuting the flags continuation condition.
497 using CanCommuteField = base::BitField8<bool, 1, 1>;
498 // MustCommuteCondField is true when we need to commute the flags continuation
499 // condition in order to switch the operands.
500 using MustCommuteCondField = base::BitField8<bool, 2, 1>;
501 // IsComparisonField is true when the operation is a comparison and has no other
502 // result other than the condition.
503 using IsComparisonField = base::BitField8<bool, 3, 1>;
504 // IsAddSubField is true when an instruction is encoded as ADD or SUB.
505 using IsAddSubField = base::BitField8<bool, 4, 1>;
506 
507 // Get properties of a binary operator.
508 uint8_t GetBinopProperties(InstructionCode opcode) {
509  uint8_t result = 0;
510  switch (opcode) {
511  case kArm64Cmp32:
512  case kArm64Cmp:
513  // We can commute CMP by switching the inputs and commuting
514  // the flags continuation.
515  result = CanCommuteField::update(result, true);
516  result = MustCommuteCondField::update(result, true);
517  result = IsComparisonField::update(result, true);
518  // The CMP and CMN instructions are encoded as SUB or ADD
519  // with zero output register, and therefore support the same
520  // operand modes.
521  result = IsAddSubField::update(result, true);
522  break;
523  case kArm64Cmn32:
524  case kArm64Cmn:
525  result = CanCommuteField::update(result, true);
526  result = IsComparisonField::update(result, true);
527  result = IsAddSubField::update(result, true);
528  break;
529  case kArm64Add32:
530  case kArm64Add:
531  result = CanCommuteField::update(result, true);
532  result = IsAddSubField::update(result, true);
533  break;
534  case kArm64Sub32:
535  case kArm64Sub:
536  result = IsAddSubField::update(result, true);
537  break;
538  case kArm64Tst32:
539  case kArm64Tst:
540  result = CanCommuteField::update(result, true);
541  result = IsComparisonField::update(result, true);
542  break;
543  case kArm64And32:
544  case kArm64And:
545  case kArm64Or32:
546  case kArm64Or:
547  case kArm64Eor32:
548  case kArm64Eor:
549  result = CanCommuteField::update(result, true);
550  break;
551  default:
552  UNREACHABLE();
553  }
554  DCHECK_IMPLIES(MustCommuteCondField::decode(result),
555  CanCommuteField::decode(result));
556  return result;
557 }
558 
559 // Shared routine for multiple binary operations.
560 template <typename Matcher>
561 void VisitBinop(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node, ArchOpcode opcode,
562  ImmediateMode operand_mode) {
563  FlagsContinuation cont;
564  VisitBinop<Matcher>(selector, node, opcode, operand_mode, &cont);
565 }
566 
567 void VisitBinopImpl(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex binop_idx,
568  OpIndex left_node, OpIndex right_node,
569  RegisterRepresentation rep, InstructionCode opcode,
570  ImmediateMode operand_mode, FlagsContinuation* cont) {
571  DCHECK(!cont->IsConditionalSet() && !cont->IsConditionalBranch());
572  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
573  constexpr uint32_t kMaxFlagSetInputs = 3;
574  constexpr uint32_t kMaxSelectInputs = 2;
575  constexpr uint32_t kMaxInputs = kMaxFlagSetInputs + kMaxSelectInputs;
576  InstructionOperand inputs[kMaxInputs];
577  size_t input_count = 0;
578  InstructionOperand outputs[1];
579  size_t output_count = 0;
580 
581  uint8_t properties = GetBinopProperties(opcode);
582  bool can_commute = CanCommuteField::decode(properties);
583  bool must_commute_cond = MustCommuteCondField::decode(properties);
584  bool is_add_sub = IsAddSubField::decode(properties);
585 
586  if (g.CanBeImmediate(right_node, operand_mode)) {
587  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(left_node);
588  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(right_node);
589  } else if (can_commute && g.CanBeImmediate(left_node, operand_mode)) {
590  if (must_commute_cond) cont->Commute();
591  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(right_node);
592  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(left_node);
593  } else if (is_add_sub &&
594  TryMatchAnyExtend(&g, selector, binop_idx, left_node, right_node,
595  &inputs[0], &inputs[1], &opcode)) {
596  input_count += 2;
597  } else if (is_add_sub && can_commute &&
598  TryMatchAnyExtend(&g, selector, binop_idx, right_node, left_node,
599  &inputs[0], &inputs[1], &opcode)) {
600  if (must_commute_cond) cont->Commute();
601  input_count += 2;
602  } else if (TryMatchAnyShift(selector, binop_idx, right_node, &opcode,
603  !is_add_sub, rep)) {
604  const ShiftOp& shift = selector->Get(right_node).Cast<ShiftOp>();
605  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegisterOrImmediateZero(left_node);
606  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(shift.left());
607  // We only need at most the last 6 bits of the shift.
608  int64_t constant;
609  selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(shift.right(), &constant);
610  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(static_cast<int>(constant & 0x3F));
611  } else if (can_commute && TryMatchAnyShift(selector, binop_idx, left_node,
612  &opcode, !is_add_sub, rep)) {
613  if (must_commute_cond) cont->Commute();
614  const ShiftOp& shift = selector->Get(left_node).Cast<ShiftOp>();
615  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegisterOrImmediateZero(right_node);
616  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(shift.left());
617  // We only need at most the last 6 bits of the shift.
618  int64_t constant;
619  selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(shift.right(), &constant);
620  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(static_cast<int>(constant & 0x3F));
621  } else {
622  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegisterOrImmediateZero(left_node);
623  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(right_node);
624  }
625 
626  if (!IsComparisonField::decode(properties)) {
627  outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(binop_idx);
628  }
629 
630  if (cont->IsSelect()) {
631  // Keep the values live until the end so that we can use operations that
632  // write registers to generate the condition, without accidently
633  // overwriting the inputs.
634  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegisterAtEnd(cont->true_value());
635  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegisterAtEnd(cont->false_value());
636  } else if (cont->IsBranch() && cont->hint() != BranchHint::kNone) {
637  opcode |= BranchHintField::encode(true);
638  }
639  DCHECK_NE(0u, input_count);
640  DCHECK((output_count != 0) || IsComparisonField::decode(properties));
641  DCHECK_GE(arraysize(inputs), input_count);
642  DCHECK_GE(arraysize(outputs), output_count);
643 
644  selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, output_count, outputs, input_count,
645  inputs, cont);
646 }
647 
648 // Shared routine for multiple binary operations.
649 void VisitBinop(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex binop_idx,
650  RegisterRepresentation rep, InstructionCode opcode,
651  ImmediateMode operand_mode, FlagsContinuation* cont) {
652  const Operation& binop = selector->Get(binop_idx);
653  OpIndex left_node = binop.input(0);
654  OpIndex right_node = binop.input(1);
655  return VisitBinopImpl(selector, binop_idx, left_node, right_node, rep, opcode,
656  operand_mode, cont);
657 }
658 
659 void VisitBinop(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
660  RegisterRepresentation rep, ArchOpcode opcode,
661  ImmediateMode operand_mode) {
662  FlagsContinuation cont;
663  VisitBinop(selector, node, rep, opcode, operand_mode, &cont);
664 }
665 
666 std::tuple<OpIndex, OpIndex> GetBinopLeftRightCstOnTheRight(
667  InstructionSelector* selector, const WordBinopOp& binop) {
668  OpIndex left = binop.left();
669  OpIndex right = binop.right();
670  if (!selector->Is<ConstantOp>(right) &&
671  WordBinopOp::IsCommutative(binop.kind) &&
672  selector->Is<ConstantOp>(left)) {
673  std::swap(left, right);
674  }
675  return {left, right};
676 }
677 
678 void VisitAddSub(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node, ArchOpcode opcode,
679  ArchOpcode negate_opcode) {
680  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
681  const WordBinopOp& add_sub = selector->Get(node).Cast<WordBinopOp>();
682  auto [left, right] = GetBinopLeftRightCstOnTheRight(selector, add_sub);
683 
684  if (std::optional<int64_t> constant_rhs =
685  g.GetOptionalIntegerConstant(right)) {
686  if (constant_rhs < 0 && constant_rhs > std::numeric_limits<int>::min() &&
687  g.CanBeImmediate(-*constant_rhs, kArithmeticImm)) {
688  selector->Emit(negate_opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
689  g.UseRegister(left),
690  g.TempImmediate(static_cast<int32_t>(-*constant_rhs)));
691  return;
692  }
693  }
694  VisitBinop(selector, node, add_sub.rep, opcode, kArithmeticImm);
695 }
696 
697 // For multiplications by immediate of the form x * (2^k + 1), where k > 0,
698 // return the value of k, otherwise return zero. This is used to reduce the
699 // multiplication to addition with left shift: x + (x << k).
700 template <typename Matcher>
701 int32_t LeftShiftForReducedMultiply(Matcher* m) {
702  DCHECK(m->IsInt32Mul() || m->IsInt64Mul());
703  if (m->right().HasResolvedValue() && m->right().ResolvedValue() >= 3) {
704  uint64_t value_minus_one = m->right().ResolvedValue() - 1;
705  if (base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(value_minus_one)) {
706  return base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(value_minus_one);
707  }
708  }
709  return 0;
710 }
711 
712 // For multiplications by immediate of the form x * (2^k + 1), where k > 0,
713 // return the value of k, otherwise return zero. This is used to reduce the
714 // multiplication to addition with left shift: x + (x << k).
715 int32_t LeftShiftForReducedMultiply(InstructionSelector* selector,
716  OpIndex rhs) {
717  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
718  if (auto constant = g.GetOptionalIntegerConstant(rhs)) {
719  int64_t value_minus_one = constant.value() - 1;
720  if (base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(value_minus_one)) {
721  return base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(value_minus_one);
722  }
723  }
724  return 0;
725 }
726 
727 // Try to match Add(Mul(x, y), z) and emit Madd(x, y, z) for it.
728 template <typename MultiplyOpmaskT>
729 bool TryEmitMultiplyAdd(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex add, OpIndex lhs,
730  OpIndex rhs, InstructionCode madd_opcode) {
731  const Operation& add_lhs = selector->Get(lhs);
732  if (!add_lhs.Is<MultiplyOpmaskT>() || !selector->CanCover(add, lhs)) {
733  return false;
734  }
735  // Check that multiply can't be reduced to an addition with shift later on.
736  const WordBinopOp& mul = add_lhs.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
737  if (LeftShiftForReducedMultiply(selector, mul.right()) != 0) return false;
738 
739  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
740  selector->Emit(madd_opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(add),
741  g.UseRegister(mul.left()), g.UseRegister(mul.right()),
742  g.UseRegister(rhs));
743  return true;
744 }
745 
746 bool TryEmitMultiplyAddInt32(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex add,
747  OpIndex lhs, OpIndex rhs) {
748  return TryEmitMultiplyAdd<Opmask::kWord32Mul>(selector, add, lhs, rhs,
749  kArm64Madd32);
750 }
751 
752 bool TryEmitMultiplyAddInt64(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex add,
753  OpIndex lhs, OpIndex rhs) {
754  return TryEmitMultiplyAdd<Opmask::kWord64Mul>(selector, add, lhs, rhs,
755  kArm64Madd);
756 }
757 
758 // Try to match Mul(Sub(0, x), y) and emit Mneg(x, y) for it.
759 template <typename SubtractOpmaskT>
760 bool TryEmitMultiplyNegate(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex mul,
761  OpIndex lhs, OpIndex rhs,
762  InstructionCode mneg_opcode) {
763  const Operation& mul_lhs = selector->Get(lhs);
764  if (!mul_lhs.Is<SubtractOpmaskT>() || !selector->CanCover(mul, lhs)) {
765  return false;
766  }
767  const WordBinopOp& sub = mul_lhs.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
768  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
769  std::optional<int64_t> sub_lhs_constant =
770  g.GetOptionalIntegerConstant(sub.left());
771  if (!sub_lhs_constant.has_value() || sub_lhs_constant != 0) return false;
772  selector->Emit(mneg_opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(mul),
773  g.UseRegister(sub.right()), g.UseRegister(rhs));
774  return true;
775 }
776 
777 bool TryEmitMultiplyNegateInt32(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex mul,
778  OpIndex lhs, OpIndex rhs) {
779  return TryEmitMultiplyNegate<Opmask::kWord32Sub>(selector, mul, lhs, rhs,
780  kArm64Mneg32);
781 }
782 
783 bool TryEmitMultiplyNegateInt64(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex mul,
784  OpIndex lhs, OpIndex rhs) {
785  return TryEmitMultiplyNegate<Opmask::kWord64Sub>(selector, mul, lhs, rhs,
786  kArm64Mneg);
787 }
788 
789 // Try to match Sub(a, Mul(x, y)) and emit Msub(x, y, a) for it.
790 template <typename MultiplyOpmaskT>
791 bool TryEmitMultiplySub(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
792  InstructionCode msub_opbocde) {
793  const WordBinopOp& sub = selector->Get(node).Cast<WordBinopOp>();
794  DCHECK_EQ(sub.kind, WordBinopOp::Kind::kSub);
795 
796  // Select Msub(x, y, a) for Sub(a, Mul(x, y)).
797  const Operation& sub_rhs = selector->Get(sub.right());
798  if (sub_rhs.Is<MultiplyOpmaskT>() && selector->CanCover(node, sub.right())) {
799  const WordBinopOp& mul = sub_rhs.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
800  if (LeftShiftForReducedMultiply(selector, mul.right()) == 0) {
801  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
802  selector->Emit(msub_opbocde, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
803  g.UseRegister(mul.left()), g.UseRegister(mul.right()),
804  g.UseRegister(sub.left()));
805  return true;
806  }
807  }
808  return false;
809 }
810 
811 std::tuple<InstructionCode, ImmediateMode> GetStoreOpcodeAndImmediate(
812  MemoryRepresentation stored_rep, bool paired) {
813  switch (stored_rep) {
814  case MemoryRepresentation::Int8():
815  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint8():
816  CHECK(!paired);
817  return {kArm64Strb, kLoadStoreImm8};
818  case MemoryRepresentation::Int16():
819  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint16():
820  CHECK(!paired);
821  return {kArm64Strh, kLoadStoreImm16};
822  case MemoryRepresentation::Int32():
823  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint32():
824  return {paired ? kArm64StrWPair : kArm64StrW, kLoadStoreImm32};
825  case MemoryRepresentation::Int64():
826  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint64():
827  return {paired ? kArm64StrPair : kArm64Str, kLoadStoreImm64};
828  case MemoryRepresentation::Float16():
829  CHECK(!paired);
830  return {kArm64StrH, kLoadStoreImm16};
831  case MemoryRepresentation::Float32():
832  CHECK(!paired);
833  return {kArm64StrS, kLoadStoreImm32};
834  case MemoryRepresentation::Float64():
835  CHECK(!paired);
836  return {kArm64StrD, kLoadStoreImm64};
837  case MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged():
838  case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer():
839  case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned():
840  if (paired) {
841  // There is an inconsistency here on how we treat stores vs. paired
842  // stores. In the normal store case we have special opcodes for
843  // compressed fields and the backend decides whether to write 32 or 64
844  // bits. However, for pairs this does not make sense, since the
845  // paired values could have different representations (e.g.,
846  // compressed paired with word32). Therefore, we decide on the actual
847  // machine representation already in instruction selection.
848 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
849  static_assert(ElementSizeLog2Of(MachineRepresentation::kTagged) == 2);
850  return {kArm64StrWPair, kLoadStoreImm32};
851 #else
852  static_assert(ElementSizeLog2Of(MachineRepresentation::kTagged) == 3);
853  return {kArm64StrPair, kLoadStoreImm64};
854 #endif
855  }
856  return {kArm64StrCompressTagged,
857  COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL ? kLoadStoreImm32 : kLoadStoreImm64};
858  case MemoryRepresentation::AnyUncompressedTagged():
859  case MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedPointer():
860  case MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedSigned():
861  CHECK(!paired);
862  return {kArm64Str, kLoadStoreImm64};
863  case MemoryRepresentation::ProtectedPointer():
864  // We never store directly to protected pointers from generated code.
865  UNREACHABLE();
866  case MemoryRepresentation::IndirectPointer():
867  return {kArm64StrIndirectPointer, kLoadStoreImm32};
868  case MemoryRepresentation::SandboxedPointer():
869  CHECK(!paired);
870  return {kArm64StrEncodeSandboxedPointer, kLoadStoreImm64};
871  case MemoryRepresentation::Simd128():
872  CHECK(!paired);
873  return {kArm64StrQ, kLoadStoreImm128};
874  case MemoryRepresentation::Simd256():
875  UNREACHABLE();
876  }
877 }

883 void InstructionSelector::VisitStackSlot(OpIndex node) {
884  const StackSlotOp& stack_slot = Cast<StackSlotOp>(node);
885  int slot = frame_->AllocateSpillSlot(stack_slot.size, stack_slot.alignment,
886  stack_slot.is_tagged);
887  OperandGenerator g(this);
888 
889  Emit(kArchStackSlot, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
890  sequence()->AddImmediate(Constant(slot)), 0, nullptr);
891 }

893 void InstructionSelector::VisitAbortCSADcheck(OpIndex node) {
894  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
895  const AbortCSADcheckOp& op = Cast<AbortCSADcheckOp>(node);
896  Emit(kArchAbortCSADcheck, g.NoOutput(), g.UseFixed(op.message(), x1));
897 }

899 void EmitLoad(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
900  InstructionCode opcode, ImmediateMode immediate_mode,
901  MemoryRepresentation rep, OptionalOpIndex output = {}) {
902  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
903  const LoadOp& load = selector->Get(node).Cast<LoadOp>();
904 
905  // The LoadStoreSimplificationReducer transforms all loads into
906  // *(base + index).
907  OpIndex base = load.base();
908  OpIndex index = load.index().value();
909  DCHECK_EQ(load.offset, 0);
910  DCHECK_EQ(load.element_size_log2, 0);
911 
912  InstructionOperand inputs[3];
913  size_t input_count = 0;
914  InstructionOperand output_op;
915 
916  // If output is valid, use that as the output register. This is used when we
917  // merge a conversion into the load.
918  output_op = g.DefineAsRegister(output.valid() ? output.value() : node);
919 
920  const Operation& base_op = selector->Get(base);
921  int64_t index_constant;
922  const bool is_index_constant =
923  selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(index, &index_constant);
924  if (base_op.Is<Opmask::kExternalConstant>() && is_index_constant) {
925  const ConstantOp& constant_base = base_op.Cast<ConstantOp>();
926  if (selector->CanAddressRelativeToRootsRegister(
927  constant_base.external_reference())) {
928  ptrdiff_t const delta =
929  index_constant +
930  MacroAssemblerBase::RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(
931  selector->isolate(), constant_base.external_reference());
932  input_count = 1;
933  // Check that the delta is a 32-bit integer due to the limitations of
934  // immediate operands.
935  if (is_int32(delta)) {
936  inputs[0] = g.UseImmediate(static_cast<int32_t>(delta));
937  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Root);
938  selector->Emit(opcode, 1, &output_op, input_count, inputs);
939  return;
940  }
941  }
942  }
943 
944  if (base_op.Is<LoadRootRegisterOp>() && is_index_constant) {
945  DCHECK(is_index_constant);
946  input_count = 1;
947  inputs[0] = g.UseImmediate64(index_constant);
948  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Root);
949  selector->Emit(opcode, 1, &output_op, input_count, inputs);
950  return;
951  }
952 
953  inputs[0] = g.UseRegister(base);
954 
955  if (is_index_constant) {
956  if (g.CanBeImmediate(index_constant, immediate_mode)) {
957  input_count = 2;
958  inputs[1] = g.UseImmediate64(index_constant);
959  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRI);
960  } else {
961  input_count = 2;
962  inputs[1] = g.UseRegister(index);
963  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRR);
964  }
965  } else {
966  if (TryMatchLoadStoreShift(&g, selector, rep, node, index, &inputs[1],
967  &inputs[2])) {
968  input_count = 3;
969  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_LSL_I);
970  } else {
971  input_count = 2;
972  inputs[1] = g.UseRegister(index);
973  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRR);
974  }
975  }
976  selector->Emit(opcode, 1, &output_op, input_count, inputs);
977 }
978 
979 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
980 namespace {
981 // Manually add base and index into a register to get the actual address.
982 // This should be used prior to instructions that only support
983 // immediate/post-index addressing, like ld1 and st1.
984 InstructionOperand EmitAddBeforeLoadOrStore(InstructionSelector* selector,
985  OpIndex node,
986  InstructionCode* opcode) {
987  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
988  *opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRI);
989  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
990  DCHECK_LE(2, op.input_count);
991  // TODO(nicohartmann): This seems brittle, we should use proper named
992  // accessors here.
993  OpIndex input0 = op.input(0);
994  OpIndex input1 = op.input(1);
995  InstructionOperand addr = g.TempRegister();
996  auto rhs = g.CanBeImmediate(input1, kArithmeticImm) ? g.UseImmediate(input1)
997  : g.UseRegister(input1);
998  selector->Emit(kArm64Add, addr, g.UseRegister(input0), rhs);
999  return addr;
1000 }
1001 } // namespace
1002 
1003 void InstructionSelector::VisitLoadLane(OpIndex node) {
1004  const Simd128LaneMemoryOp& load = Cast<Simd128LaneMemoryOp>(node);
1005  InstructionCode opcode = kArm64LoadLane;
1006  opcode |= LaneSizeField::encode(load.lane_size() * kBitsPerByte);
1007  if (load.kind.with_trap_handler) {
1008  opcode |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
1009  }
1010 
1011  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
1012  InstructionOperand addr = EmitAddBeforeLoadOrStore(this, node, &opcode);
1013  Emit(opcode, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(load.value()),
1014  g.UseImmediate(load.lane), addr, g.TempImmediate(0));
1015 }
1016 
1017 void InstructionSelector::VisitStoreLane(OpIndex node) {
1018  const Simd128LaneMemoryOp& store = Cast<Simd128LaneMemoryOp>(node);
1019  InstructionCode opcode = kArm64StoreLane;
1020  opcode |= LaneSizeField::encode(store.lane_size() * kBitsPerByte);
1021  if (store.kind.with_trap_handler) {
1022  opcode |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
1023  }
1024 
1025  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
1026  InstructionOperand addr = EmitAddBeforeLoadOrStore(this, node, &opcode);
1027  InstructionOperand inputs[4] = {
1028  g.UseRegister(store.value()),
1029  g.UseImmediate(store.lane),
1030  addr,
1031  g.TempImmediate(0),
1032  };
1033 
1034  Emit(opcode, 0, nullptr, 4, inputs);
1035 }
1036 
1037 void InstructionSelector::VisitLoadTransform(OpIndex node) {
1038  const Simd128LoadTransformOp& op = Cast<Simd128LoadTransformOp>(node);
1039  InstructionCode opcode = kArchNop;
1040  bool require_add = false;
1041  switch (op.transform_kind) {
1042  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k8Splat:
1043  opcode = kArm64LoadSplat;
1044  opcode |= LaneSizeField::encode(8);
1045  require_add = true;
1046  break;
1047  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k16Splat:
1048  opcode = kArm64LoadSplat;
1049  opcode |= LaneSizeField::encode(16);
1050  require_add = true;
1051  break;
1052  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k32Splat:
1053  opcode = kArm64LoadSplat;
1054  opcode |= LaneSizeField::encode(32);
1055  require_add = true;
1056  break;
1057  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k64Splat:
1058  opcode = kArm64LoadSplat;
1059  opcode |= LaneSizeField::encode(64);
1060  require_add = true;
1061  break;
1062  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k8x8S:
1063  opcode = kArm64S128Load8x8S;
1064  break;
1065  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k8x8U:
1066  opcode = kArm64S128Load8x8U;
1067  break;
1068  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k16x4S:
1069  opcode = kArm64S128Load16x4S;
1070  break;
1071  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k16x4U:
1072  opcode = kArm64S128Load16x4U;
1073  break;
1074  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k32x2S:
1075  opcode = kArm64S128Load32x2S;
1076  break;
1077  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k32x2U:
1078  opcode = kArm64S128Load32x2U;
1079  break;
1080  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k32Zero:
1081  opcode = kArm64LdrS;
1082  break;
1083  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k64Zero:
1084  opcode = kArm64LdrD;
1085  break;
1086  default:
1087  UNIMPLEMENTED();
1088  }
1089  // ARM64 supports unaligned loads
1090  DCHECK(!op.load_kind.maybe_unaligned);
1091 
1092  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
1093  InstructionOperand inputs[2];
1094  InstructionOperand outputs[1];
1095 
1096  inputs[0] = g.UseRegister(op.base());
1097  inputs[1] = g.UseRegister(op.index());
1098  outputs[0] = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
1099 
1100  if (require_add) {
1101  // ld1r uses post-index, so construct address first.
1102  // TODO(v8:9886) If index can be immediate, use vldr without this add.
1103  inputs[0] = EmitAddBeforeLoadOrStore(this, node, &opcode);
1104  inputs[1] = g.TempImmediate(0);
1105  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRI);
1106  } else {
1107  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRR);
1108  }
1109  if (op.load_kind.with_trap_handler) {
1110  opcode |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
1111  }
1112  Emit(opcode, 1, outputs, 2, inputs);
1113 }
1114 
1115 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1116 
1117 std::tuple<InstructionCode, ImmediateMode> GetLoadOpcodeAndImmediate(
1118  MemoryRepresentation loaded_rep, RegisterRepresentation result_rep) {
1119  // NOTE: The meaning of `loaded_rep` = `MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged()` is
1120  // we are loading a compressed tagged field, while `result_rep` =
1121  // `RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()` refers to an uncompressed tagged value.
1122  switch (loaded_rep) {
1123  case MemoryRepresentation::Int8():
1124  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
1125  return {kArm64LdrsbW, kLoadStoreImm8};
1126  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint8():
1127  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
1128  return {kArm64Ldrb, kLoadStoreImm8};
1129  case MemoryRepresentation::Int16():
1130  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
1131  return {kArm64LdrshW, kLoadStoreImm16};
1132  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint16():
1133  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
1134  return {kArm64Ldrh, kLoadStoreImm16};
1135  case MemoryRepresentation::Int32():
1136  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint32():
1137  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
1138  return {kArm64LdrW, kLoadStoreImm32};
1139  case MemoryRepresentation::Int64():
1140  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint64():
1141  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word64());
1142  return {kArm64Ldr, kLoadStoreImm64};
1143  case MemoryRepresentation::Float16():
1144  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Float32());
1145  return {kArm64LdrH, kLoadStoreImm16};
1146  case MemoryRepresentation::Float32():
1147  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Float32());
1148  return {kArm64LdrS, kLoadStoreImm32};
1149  case MemoryRepresentation::Float64():
1150  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Float64());
1151  return {kArm64LdrD, kLoadStoreImm64};
1152 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
1153  case MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged():
1154  case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer():
1155  if (result_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Compressed()) {
1156  return {kArm64LdrW, kLoadStoreImm32};
1157  }
1158  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
1159  return {kArm64LdrDecompressTagged, kLoadStoreImm32};
1160  case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned():
1161  if (result_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Compressed()) {
1162  return {kArm64LdrW, kLoadStoreImm32};
1163  }
1164  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
1165  return {kArm64LdrDecompressTaggedSigned, kLoadStoreImm32};
1166 #else
1167  case MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged():
1168  case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer():
1169  case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned():
1170  return {kArm64Ldr, kLoadStoreImm64};
1171 #endif
1172  case MemoryRepresentation::AnyUncompressedTagged():
1173  case MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedPointer():
1174  case MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedSigned():
1175  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
1176  return {kArm64Ldr, kLoadStoreImm64};
1177  case MemoryRepresentation::ProtectedPointer():
1178  CHECK(V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
1179  return {kArm64LdrDecompressProtected, kNoImmediate};
1180  case MemoryRepresentation::IndirectPointer():
1181  UNREACHABLE();
1182  case MemoryRepresentation::SandboxedPointer():
1183  return {kArm64LdrDecodeSandboxedPointer, kLoadStoreImm64};
1184  case MemoryRepresentation::Simd128():
1185  return {kArm64LdrQ, kLoadStoreImm128};
1186  case MemoryRepresentation::Simd256():
1187  UNREACHABLE();
1188  }
1189 }
1190 
1191 void InstructionSelector::VisitLoad(OpIndex node) {
1192  InstructionCode opcode = kArchNop;
1193  ImmediateMode immediate_mode = kNoImmediate;
1194  auto load = load_view(node);
1195  MemoryRepresentation load_rep = load.ts_loaded_rep();
1196  std::tie(opcode, immediate_mode) =
1197  GetLoadOpcodeAndImmediate(load_rep, load.ts_result_rep());
1198  bool traps_on_null;
1199  if (load.is_protected(&traps_on_null)) {
1200  if (traps_on_null) {
1201  opcode |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedNullDereference);
1202  } else {
1203  opcode |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
1204  }
1205  }
1206  EmitLoad(this, node, opcode, immediate_mode, load_rep);
1207 }
1208 
1209 void InstructionSelector::VisitProtectedLoad(OpIndex node) { VisitLoad(node); }
1210 
1211 void InstructionSelector::VisitStorePair(OpIndex node) {
1212  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
1213  UNIMPLEMENTED();
1214 }
1215 
1216 void InstructionSelector::VisitStore(OpIndex node) {
1217  StoreView store_view = this->store_view(node);
1218  DCHECK_EQ(store_view.displacement(), 0);
1219  WriteBarrierKind write_barrier_kind =
1220  store_view.stored_rep().write_barrier_kind();
1221  const MemoryRepresentation store_rep = store_view.ts_stored_rep();
1222  const MachineRepresentation representation =
1223  store_view.stored_rep().representation();
1224 
1225  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
1226 
1227  // TODO(arm64): I guess this could be done in a better way.
1228  if (write_barrier_kind != kNoWriteBarrier &&
1229  !v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) {
1230  DCHECK(CanBeTaggedOrCompressedOrIndirectPointer(representation));
1231  AddressingMode addressing_mode;
1232  InstructionOperand inputs[4];
1233  size_t input_count = 0;
1234  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(store_view.base());
1235  // OutOfLineRecordWrite uses the index in an add or sub instruction, but we
1236  // can trust the assembler to generate extra instructions if the index does
1237  // not fit into add or sub. So here only check the immediate for a store.
1238  OpIndex index = store_view.index().value();
1239  if (g.CanBeImmediate(index, COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL ? kLoadStoreImm32
1240  : kLoadStoreImm64)) {
1241  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(index);
1242  addressing_mode = kMode_MRI;
1243  } else {
1244  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(index);
1245  addressing_mode = kMode_MRR;
1246  }
1247  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(store_view.value());
1248  RecordWriteMode record_write_mode =
1249  WriteBarrierKindToRecordWriteMode(write_barrier_kind);
1250  InstructionCode code;
1251  if (store_rep == MemoryRepresentation::IndirectPointer()) {
1252  DCHECK_EQ(write_barrier_kind, kIndirectPointerWriteBarrier);
1253  // In this case we need to add the IndirectPointerTag as additional input.
1254  code = kArchStoreIndirectWithWriteBarrier;
1255  IndirectPointerTag tag = store_view.indirect_pointer_tag();
1256  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate64(static_cast<int64_t>(tag));
1257  } else {
1258  code = kArchStoreWithWriteBarrier;
1259  }
1260  code |= AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
1261  code |= RecordWriteModeField::encode(record_write_mode);
1262  if (store_view.is_store_trap_on_null()) {
1263  code |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedNullDereference);
1264  }
1265  Emit(code, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs);
1266  return;
1267  }
1268 
1269  InstructionOperand inputs[4];
1270  size_t input_count = 0;
1271 
1272  InstructionCode opcode;
1273  ImmediateMode immediate_mode;
1274  std::tie(opcode, immediate_mode) =
1275  GetStoreOpcodeAndImmediate(store_rep, false);
1276 
1277  if (v8_flags.enable_unconditional_write_barriers) {
1278  if (CanBeTaggedOrCompressedPointer(representation)) {
1279  write_barrier_kind = kFullWriteBarrier;
1280  }
1281  }
1282 
1283  std::optional<ExternalReference> external_base;
1284  ExternalReference value;
1285  if (this->MatchExternalConstant(store_view.base(), &value)) {
1286  external_base = value;
1287  }
1288 
1289  std::optional<int64_t> constant_index;
1290  if (store_view.index().valid()) {
1291  OpIndex index = store_view.index().value();
1292  constant_index = g.GetOptionalIntegerConstant(index);
1293  }
1294  if (external_base.has_value() && constant_index.has_value() &&
1295  CanAddressRelativeToRootsRegister(*external_base)) {
1296  ptrdiff_t const delta =
1297  *constant_index +
1298  MacroAssemblerBase::RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(
1299  isolate(), *external_base);
1300  if (is_int32(delta)) {
1301  input_count = 2;
1302  InstructionOperand inputs[2];
1303  inputs[0] = g.UseRegister(store_view.value());
1304  inputs[1] = g.UseImmediate(static_cast<int32_t>(delta));
1305  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Root);
1306  Emit(opcode, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs);
1307  return;
1308  }
1309  }
1310 
1311  OpIndex base = store_view.base();
1312  OpIndex index = store_view.index().value();
1313 
1314  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegisterOrImmediateZero(store_view.value());
1315 
1316  if (Is<LoadRootRegisterOp>(base)) {
1317  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(index);
1318  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Root);
1319  Emit(opcode, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs);
1320  return;
1321  }
1322 
1323  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(base);
1324 
1325  if (g.CanBeImmediate(index, immediate_mode)) {
1326  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(index);
1327  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRI);
1328  } else if (TryMatchLoadStoreShift(&g, this, store_rep, node, index,
1329  &inputs[input_count],
1330  &inputs[input_count + 1])) {
1331  input_count += 2;
1332  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_LSL_I);
1333  } else {
1334  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(index);
1335  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRR);
1336  }
1337 
1338  if (store_view.is_store_trap_on_null()) {
1339  opcode |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedNullDereference);
1340  } else if (store_view.access_kind() ==
1341  MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler) {
1342  opcode |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
1343  }
1344 
1345  Emit(opcode, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs);
1346 }
1347 
1348 void InstructionSelector::VisitProtectedStore(OpIndex node) {
1349  VisitStore(node);
1350 }

1353  UNREACHABLE();
1354 }

1357 void InstructionSelector::VisitUnalignedLoad(OpIndex node) { UNREACHABLE(); }

1360 void InstructionSelector::VisitUnalignedStore(OpIndex node) { UNREACHABLE(); }

1362 namespace turboshaft {
1363 
1364 class CompareSequence {
1365  public:
1366  void InitialCompare(OpIndex op, OpIndex l, OpIndex r,
1367  RegisterRepresentation rep) {
1368  DCHECK(!HasCompare());
1369  cmp_ = op;
1370  left_ = l;
1371  right_ = r;
1372  opcode_ = GetOpcode(rep);
1373  }
1374  bool HasCompare() const { return cmp_.valid(); }
1375  OpIndex cmp() const { return cmp_; }
1376  OpIndex left() const { return left_; }
1377  OpIndex right() const { return right_; }
1378  InstructionCode opcode() const { return opcode_; }
1379  uint32_t num_ccmps() const { return num_ccmps_; }
1380  FlagsContinuation::compare_chain_t& ccmps() { return ccmps_; }
1381  void AddConditionalCompare(RegisterRepresentation rep,
1382  FlagsCondition ccmp_condition,
1383  FlagsCondition default_flags, OpIndex ccmp_lhs,
1384  OpIndex ccmp_rhs) {
1385  InstructionCode code = GetOpcode(rep);
1386  ccmps_.at(num_ccmps_) = FlagsContinuation::ConditionalCompare{
1387  code, ccmp_condition, default_flags, ccmp_lhs, ccmp_rhs};
1388  ++num_ccmps_;
1389  }
1390  bool IsFloatCmp() const {
1391  return opcode() == kArm64Float32Cmp || opcode() == kArm64Float64Cmp;
1392  }
1393 
1394  private:
1395  InstructionCode GetOpcode(RegisterRepresentation rep) const {
1396  switch (rep.MapTaggedToWord().value()) {
1397  case RegisterRepresentation::Word32():
1398  return kArm64Cmp32;
1399  case RegisterRepresentation::Word64():
1400  return kArm64Cmp;
1401  case RegisterRepresentation::Float32():
1402  return kArm64Float32Cmp;
1403  case RegisterRepresentation::Float64():
1404  return kArm64Float64Cmp;
1405  default:
1406  UNREACHABLE();
1407  }
1408  }
1409 
1410  OpIndex cmp_;
1411  OpIndex left_;
1412  OpIndex right_;
1413  InstructionCode opcode_;
1414  FlagsContinuation::compare_chain_t ccmps_;
1415  uint32_t num_ccmps_ = 0;
1416 };
1417 
1418 class CompareChainNode final : public ZoneObject {
1419  public:
1420  enum class NodeKind : uint8_t { kFlagSetting, kLogicalCombine };
1421 
1422  explicit CompareChainNode(OpIndex n, FlagsCondition condition)
1423  : node_kind_(NodeKind::kFlagSetting),
1424  user_condition_(condition),
1425  node_(n) {}
1426 
1427  explicit CompareChainNode(OpIndex n, CompareChainNode* l, CompareChainNode* r)
1428  : node_kind_(NodeKind::kLogicalCombine), node_(n), lhs_(l), rhs_(r) {
1429  // Canonicalise the chain with cmps on the right.
1430  if (lhs_->IsFlagSetting() && !rhs_->IsFlagSetting()) {
1431  std::swap(lhs_, rhs_);
1432  }
1433  }
1434  void SetCondition(FlagsCondition condition) {
1435  DCHECK(IsLogicalCombine());
1436  user_condition_ = condition;
1437  if (requires_negation_) {
1438  NegateFlags();
1439  }
1440  }
1441  void MarkRequiresNegation() {
1442  if (IsFlagSetting()) {
1443  NegateFlags();
1444  } else {
1445  requires_negation_ = !requires_negation_;
1446  }
1447  }
1448  void NegateFlags() {
1449  user_condition_ = NegateFlagsCondition(user_condition_);
1450  requires_negation_ = false;
1451  }
1452  bool IsLegalFirstCombine() const {
1453  DCHECK(IsLogicalCombine());
1454  // We need two cmps feeding the first logic op.
1455  return lhs_->IsFlagSetting() && rhs_->IsFlagSetting();
1456  }
1457  bool IsFlagSetting() const { return node_kind_ == NodeKind::kFlagSetting; }
1458  bool IsLogicalCombine() const {
1459  return node_kind_ == NodeKind::kLogicalCombine;
1460  }
1461  OpIndex node() const { return node_; }
1462  FlagsCondition user_condition() const { return user_condition_; }
1463  CompareChainNode* lhs() const {
1464  DCHECK(IsLogicalCombine());
1465  return lhs_;
1466  }
1467  CompareChainNode* rhs() const {
1468  DCHECK(IsLogicalCombine());
1469  return rhs_;
1470  }
1471 
1472  private:
1473  NodeKind node_kind_;
1474  FlagsCondition user_condition_;
1475  bool requires_negation_ = false;
1476  OpIndex node_;
1477  CompareChainNode* lhs_ = nullptr;
1478  CompareChainNode* rhs_ = nullptr;
1479 };
1480 
1481 static std::optional<FlagsCondition> GetFlagsCondition(
1482  OpIndex node, InstructionSelector* selector) {
1483  if (const ComparisonOp* comparison =
1484  selector->Get(node).TryCast<ComparisonOp>()) {
1485  if (comparison->rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32() ||
1486  comparison->rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word64() ||
1487  comparison->rep == RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()) {
1488  switch (comparison->kind) {
1489  case ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual:
1490  return FlagsCondition::kEqual;
1491  case ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan:
1492  return FlagsCondition::kSignedLessThan;
1493  case ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual:
1494  return FlagsCondition::kSignedLessThanOrEqual;
1495  case ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThan:
1496  return FlagsCondition::kUnsignedLessThan;
1497  case ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual:
1498  return FlagsCondition::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual;
1499  default:
1500  UNREACHABLE();
1501  }
1502  } else if (comparison->rep == RegisterRepresentation::Float32() ||
1503  comparison->rep == RegisterRepresentation::Float64()) {
1504  switch (comparison->kind) {
1505  case ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual:
1506  return FlagsCondition::kEqual;
1507  case ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan:
1508  return FlagsCondition::kFloatLessThan;
1509  case ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual:
1510  return FlagsCondition::kFloatLessThanOrEqual;
1511  default:
1512  UNREACHABLE();
1513  }
1514  }
1515  }
1516  return std::nullopt;
1517 }
1518 
1519 // Search through AND, OR and comparisons.
1520 // To make life a little easier, we currently don't handle combining two logic
1521 // operations. There are restrictions on what logical combinations can be
1522 // performed with ccmp, so this implementation builds a ccmp chain from the LHS
1523 // of the tree while combining one more compare from the RHS at each step. So,
1524 // currently, if we discover a pattern like this:
1525 // logic(logic(cmp, cmp), logic(cmp, cmp))
1526 // The search will fail from the outermost logic operation, but it will succeed
1527 // for the two inner operations. This will result in, suboptimal, codegen:
1528 // cmp
1529 // ccmp
1530 // cset x
1531 // cmp
1532 // ccmp
1533 // cset y
1534 // logic x, y
1535 static std::optional<CompareChainNode*> FindCompareChain(
1536  OpIndex user, OpIndex node, InstructionSelector* selector, Zone* zone,
1537  ZoneVector<CompareChainNode*>& nodes) {
1538  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
1539  if (op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>() || op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseOr>()) {
1540  const WordBinopOp& binop = op.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
1541  auto maybe_lhs =
1542  FindCompareChain(node, binop.left(), selector, zone, nodes);
1543  auto maybe_rhs =
1544  FindCompareChain(node, binop.right(), selector, zone, nodes);
1545  if (maybe_lhs.has_value() && maybe_rhs.has_value()) {
1546  CompareChainNode* lhs = maybe_lhs.value();
1547  CompareChainNode* rhs = maybe_rhs.value();
1548  // Ensure we don't try to combine a logic operation with two logic inputs.
1549  if (lhs->IsFlagSetting() || rhs->IsFlagSetting()) {
1550  nodes.push_back(std::move(zone->New<CompareChainNode>(node, lhs, rhs)));
1551  return nodes.back();
1552  }
1553  }
1554  // Ensure we remove any valid sub-trees that now cannot be used.
1555  nodes.clear();
1556  return std::nullopt;
1557  } else if (user.valid() && selector->CanCover(user, node)) {
1558  std::optional<FlagsCondition> user_condition =
1559  GetFlagsCondition(node, selector);
1560  if (!user_condition.has_value()) {
1561  return std::nullopt;
1562  }
1563  const ComparisonOp& comparison = selector->Cast<ComparisonOp>(node);
1564  if (comparison.kind == ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual &&
1565  selector->MatchIntegralZero(comparison.right())) {
1566  auto maybe_negated =
1567  FindCompareChain(node, comparison.left(), selector, zone, nodes);
1568  if (maybe_negated.has_value()) {
1569  CompareChainNode* negated = maybe_negated.value();
1570  negated->MarkRequiresNegation();
1571  return negated;
1572  }
1573  }
1574  return zone->New<CompareChainNode>(node, user_condition.value());
1575  }
1576  return std::nullopt;
1577 }
1578 
1579 // Overview -------------------------------------------------------------------
1580 //
1581 // A compare operation will generate a 'user condition', which is the
1582 // FlagCondition of the opcode. For this algorithm, we generate the default
1583 // flags from the LHS of the logic op, while the RHS is used to predicate the
1584 // new ccmp. Depending on the logical user, those conditions are either used
1585 // as-is or negated:
1586 // > For OR, the generated ccmp will negate the LHS condition for its predicate
1587 // while the default flags are taken from the RHS.
1588 // > For AND, the generated ccmp will take the LHS condition for its predicate
1589 // while the default flags are a negation of the RHS.
1590 //
1591 // The new ccmp will now generate a user condition of its own, and this is
1592 // always forwarded from the RHS.
1593 //
1594 // Chaining compares, including with OR, needs to be equivalent to combining
1595 // all the results with AND, and NOT.
1596 //
1597 // AND Example ----------------------------------------------------------------
1598 //
1599 // cmpA cmpB
1600 // | |
1601 // condA condB
1602 // | |
1603 // --- AND ---
1604 //
1605 // As the AND becomes the ccmp, it is predicated on condA and the cset is
1606 // predicated on condB. The user of the ccmp is always predicated on the
1607 // condition from the RHS of the logic operation. The default flags are
1608 // not(condB) so cset only produces one when both condA and condB are true:
1609 // cmpA
1610 // ccmpB not(condB), condA
1611 // cset condB
1612 //
1613 // OR Example -----------------------------------------------------------------
1614 //
1615 // cmpA cmpB
1616 // | |
1617 // condA condB
1618 // | |
1619 // --- OR ---
1620 //
1621 // cmpA cmpB
1622 // equivalent -> | |
1623 // not(condA) not(condB)
1624 // | |
1625 // ----- AND -----
1626 // |
1627 // NOT
1628 //
1629 // In this case, the input conditions to the AND (the ccmp) have been negated
1630 // so the user condition and default flags have been negated compared to the
1631 // previous example. The cset still uses condB because it is negated twice:
1632 // cmpA
1633 // ccmpB condB, not(condA)
1634 // cset condB
1635 //
1636 // Combining AND and OR -------------------------------------------------------
1637 //
1638 // cmpA cmpB cmpC
1639 // | | |
1640 // condA condB condC
1641 // | | |
1642 // --- AND --- |
1643 // | |
1644 // OR -----------
1645 //
1646 // equivalent -> cmpA cmpB cmpC
1647 // | | |
1648 // condA condB not(condC)
1649 // | | |
1650 // --- AND --- |
1651 // | |
1652 // NOT |
1653 // | |
1654 // AND -------------
1655 // |
1656 // NOT
1657 //
1658 // For this example the 'user condition', coming out, of the first ccmp is
1659 // condB but it is negated as the input predicate for the next ccmp as that
1660 // one is performing an OR:
1661 // cmpA
1662 // ccmpB not(condB), condA
1663 // ccmpC condC, not(condB)
1664 // cset condC
1665 //
1666 void CombineFlagSettingOps(CompareChainNode* logic_node,
1667  InstructionSelector* selector,
1668  CompareSequence* sequence) {
1669  CompareChainNode* lhs = logic_node->lhs();
1670  CompareChainNode* rhs = logic_node->rhs();
1671 
1672  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
1673  if (!sequence->HasCompare()) {
1674  // This is the beginning of the conditional compare chain.
1675  DCHECK(lhs->IsFlagSetting());
1676  DCHECK(rhs->IsFlagSetting());
1677 
1678  {
1679  // ccmp has a much smaller immediate range than cmp, so swap the
1680  // operations if possible.
1681  OpIndex cmp = lhs->node();
1682  OpIndex ccmp = rhs->node();
1683  const Operation& cmp_op = selector->Get(cmp);
1684  const Operation& ccmp_op = selector->Get(ccmp);
1685  OpIndex cmp_right = cmp_op.input(1);
1686  OpIndex ccmp_right = ccmp_op.input(1);
1687  if (g.CanBeImmediate(cmp_right, kConditionalCompareImm) &&
1688  !g.CanBeImmediate(ccmp_right, kConditionalCompareImm)) {
1689  // If the ccmp could use the cmp immediate, swap them.
1690  std::swap(lhs, rhs);
1691  } else if (g.CanBeImmediate(ccmp_right, kArithmeticImm) &&
1692  !g.CanBeImmediate(ccmp_right, kConditionalCompareImm)) {
1693  // If the ccmp can't use its immediate, but a cmp could, swap them.
1694  std::swap(lhs, rhs);
1695  }
1696  }
1697  OpIndex cmp = lhs->node();
1698  const ComparisonOp& cmp_op = selector->Cast<ComparisonOp>(cmp);
1699 
1700  // Initialize chain with the compare which will hold the continuation.
1701  sequence->InitialCompare(cmp, cmp_op.left(), cmp_op.right(), cmp_op.rep);
1702  }
1703 
1704  bool is_logical_or =
1705  selector->Get(logic_node->node()).Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseOr>();
1706  FlagsCondition ccmp_condition =
1707  is_logical_or ? NegateFlagsCondition(lhs->user_condition())
1708  : lhs->user_condition();
1709  FlagsCondition default_flags =
1710  is_logical_or ? rhs->user_condition()
1711  : NegateFlagsCondition(rhs->user_condition());
1712 
1713  // We canonicalise the chain so that the rhs is always a cmp, whereas lhs
1714  // will either be the initial cmp or the previous logic, now ccmp, op and
1715  // only provides ccmp_condition.
1716  FlagsCondition user_condition = rhs->user_condition();
1717  OpIndex ccmp = rhs->node();
1718  const ComparisonOp& ccmp_op = selector->Cast<ComparisonOp>(ccmp);
1719  OpIndex ccmp_lhs = ccmp_op.left();
1720  OpIndex ccmp_rhs = ccmp_op.right();
1721 
1722  // Switch ccmp lhs/rhs if lhs is a small immediate.
1723  if (g.CanBeImmediate(ccmp_lhs, kConditionalCompareImm)) {
1724  user_condition = CommuteFlagsCondition(user_condition);
1725  default_flags = CommuteFlagsCondition(default_flags);
1726  std::swap(ccmp_lhs, ccmp_rhs);
1727  }
1728 
1729  sequence->AddConditionalCompare(ccmp_op.rep, ccmp_condition, default_flags,
1730  ccmp_lhs, ccmp_rhs);
1731  // Ensure the user_condition is kept up-to-date for the next ccmp/cset.
1732  logic_node->SetCondition(user_condition);
1733 }
1734 
1735 static std::optional<FlagsCondition> TryMatchConditionalCompareChainShared(
1736  InstructionSelector* selector, Zone* zone, OpIndex node,
1737  CompareSequence* sequence) {
1738  // Instead of:
1739  // cmp x0, y0
1740  // cset cc0
1741  // cmp x1, y1
1742  // cset cc1
1743  // and/orr
1744  // Try to merge logical combinations of flags into:
1745  // cmp x0, y0
1746  // ccmp x1, y1 ..
1747  // cset ..
1748  // So, for AND:
1749  // (cset cc1 (ccmp x1 y1 !cc1 cc0 (cmp x0, y0)))
1750  // and for ORR:
1751  // (cset cc1 (ccmp x1 y1 cc1 !cc0 (cmp x0, y0))
1752 
1753  // Look for a potential chain.
1754  ZoneVector<CompareChainNode*> logic_nodes(zone);
1755  auto root =
1756  FindCompareChain(OpIndex::Invalid(), node, selector, zone, logic_nodes);
1757  if (!root.has_value()) return std::nullopt;
1758 
1759  if (logic_nodes.size() > FlagsContinuation::kMaxCompareChainSize) {
1760  return std::nullopt;
1761  }
1762  if (!logic_nodes.front()->IsLegalFirstCombine()) {
1763  return std::nullopt;
1764  }
1765 
1766  for (auto* logic_node : logic_nodes) {
1767  CombineFlagSettingOps(logic_node, selector, sequence);
1768  }
1769  DCHECK_LE(sequence->num_ccmps(), FlagsContinuation::kMaxCompareChainSize);
1770  return logic_nodes.back()->user_condition();
1771 }
1772 
1773 static void VisitCompareChain(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex left_node,
1774  OpIndex right_node, RegisterRepresentation rep,
1775  InstructionCode opcode,
1776  ImmediateMode operand_mode,
1777  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
1778  DCHECK(cont->IsConditionalSet() || cont->IsConditionalBranch());
1779  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
1780  constexpr uint32_t kMaxFlagSetInputs = 2;
1781  constexpr uint32_t kMaxCcmpOperands =
1782  FlagsContinuation::kMaxCompareChainSize * kNumCcmpOperands;
1783  constexpr uint32_t kExtraCcmpInputs = 2;
1784  constexpr uint32_t kMaxInputs =
1785  kMaxFlagSetInputs + kMaxCcmpOperands + kExtraCcmpInputs;
1786  InstructionOperand inputs[kMaxInputs];
1787  size_t input_count = 0;
1788 
1789  if (g.CanBeImmediate(right_node, operand_mode)) {
1790  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(left_node);
1791  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(right_node);
1792  } else {
1793  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegisterOrImmediateZero(left_node);
1794  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(right_node);
1795  }
1796 
1797  auto& compares = cont->compares();
1798  for (unsigned i = 0; i < cont->num_conditional_compares(); ++i) {
1799  auto compare = compares[i];
1800  inputs[input_count + kCcmpOffsetOfOpcode] = g.TempImmediate(compare.code);
1801  inputs[input_count + kCcmpOffsetOfLhs] = g.UseRegisterAtEnd(compare.lhs);
1802  if ((compare.code == kArm64Cmp32 || compare.code == kArm64Cmp) &&
1803  g.CanBeImmediate(compare.rhs, kConditionalCompareImm)) {
1804  inputs[input_count + kCcmpOffsetOfRhs] = g.UseImmediate(compare.rhs);
1805  } else {
1806  inputs[input_count + kCcmpOffsetOfRhs] = g.UseRegisterAtEnd(compare.rhs);
1807  }
1808  inputs[input_count + kCcmpOffsetOfDefaultFlags] =
1809  g.TempImmediate(compare.default_flags);
1810  inputs[input_count + kCcmpOffsetOfCompareCondition] =
1811  g.TempImmediate(compare.compare_condition);
1812  input_count += kNumCcmpOperands;
1813  }
1814  inputs[input_count++] = g.TempImmediate(cont->final_condition());
1815  inputs[input_count++] =
1816  g.TempImmediate(static_cast<int32_t>(cont->num_conditional_compares()));
1817 
1818  DCHECK_GE(arraysize(inputs), input_count);
1819 
1820  selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs, cont);
1821 }
1822 
1823 static bool TryMatchConditionalCompareChainBranch(InstructionSelector* selector,
1824  Zone* zone, OpIndex node,
1825  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
1826  if (!cont->IsBranch()) return false;
1827  DCHECK(cont->condition() == kNotEqual || cont->condition() == kEqual);
1828 
1829  CompareSequence sequence;
1830  auto final_cond =
1831  TryMatchConditionalCompareChainShared(selector, zone, node, &sequence);
1832  if (final_cond.has_value()) {
1833  FlagsCondition condition = cont->condition() == kNotEqual
1834  ? final_cond.value()
1835  : NegateFlagsCondition(final_cond.value());
1836  FlagsContinuation new_cont = FlagsContinuation::ForConditionalBranch(
1837  sequence.ccmps(), sequence.num_ccmps(), condition, cont->true_block(),
1838  cont->false_block());
1839 
1840  ImmediateMode imm_mode =
1841  sequence.IsFloatCmp() ? kNoImmediate : kArithmeticImm;
1842  VisitCompareChain(selector, sequence.left(), sequence.right(),
1843  selector->Get(sequence.cmp()).Cast<ComparisonOp>().rep,
1844  sequence.opcode(), imm_mode, &new_cont);
1845 
1846  return true;
1847  }
1848  return false;
1849 }
1850 
1851 static bool TryMatchConditionalCompareChainSet(InstructionSelector* selector,
1852  Zone* zone, OpIndex node) {
1853  // Create the cmp + ccmp ... sequence.
1854  CompareSequence sequence;
1855  auto final_cond =
1856  TryMatchConditionalCompareChainShared(selector, zone, node, &sequence);
1857  if (final_cond.has_value()) {
1858  // The continuation performs the conditional compare and cset.
1859  FlagsContinuation cont = FlagsContinuation::ForConditionalSet(
1860  sequence.ccmps(), sequence.num_ccmps(), final_cond.value(), node);
1861 
1862  ImmediateMode imm_mode =
1863  sequence.IsFloatCmp() ? kNoImmediate : kArithmeticImm;
1864  VisitCompareChain(selector, sequence.left(), sequence.right(),
1865  selector->Get(sequence.cmp()).Cast<ComparisonOp>().rep,
1866  sequence.opcode(), imm_mode, &cont);
1867  return true;
1868  }
1869  return false;
1870 }
1871 
1872 } // end namespace turboshaft
1873 
1874 static void VisitLogical(InstructionSelector* selector, Zone* zone,
1875  OpIndex node, WordRepresentation rep,
1876  ArchOpcode opcode, bool left_can_cover,
1877  bool right_can_cover, ImmediateMode imm_mode) {
1878  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
1879  const WordBinopOp& logical_op = selector->Get(node).Cast<WordBinopOp>();
1880  const Operation& lhs = selector->Get(logical_op.left());
1881  const Operation& rhs = selector->Get(logical_op.right());
1882 
1883  // Map instruction to equivalent operation with inverted right input.
1884  ArchOpcode inv_opcode = opcode;
1885  switch (opcode) {
1886  case kArm64And32:
1887  inv_opcode = kArm64Bic32;
1888  break;
1889  case kArm64And:
1890  inv_opcode = kArm64Bic;
1891  break;
1892  case kArm64Or32:
1893  inv_opcode = kArm64Orn32;
1894  break;
1895  case kArm64Or:
1896  inv_opcode = kArm64Orn;
1897  break;
1898  case kArm64Eor32:
1899  inv_opcode = kArm64Eon32;
1900  break;
1901  case kArm64Eor:
1902  inv_opcode = kArm64Eon;
1903  break;
1904  default:
1905  UNREACHABLE();
1906  }
1907 
1908  if (TryMatchConditionalCompareChainSet(selector, zone, node)) {
1909  return;
1910  }
1911 
1912  // Select Logical(y, ~x) for Logical(Xor(x, -1), y).
1913  if (lhs.Is<Opmask::kBitwiseXor>() && left_can_cover) {
1914  const WordBinopOp& xor_op = lhs.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
1915  int64_t xor_rhs_val;
1916  if (selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(xor_op.right(), &xor_rhs_val) &&
1917  xor_rhs_val == -1) {
1918  // TODO(all): support shifted operand on right.
1919  selector->Emit(inv_opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
1920  g.UseRegister(logical_op.right()),
1921  g.UseRegister(xor_op.left()));
1922  return;
1923  }
1924  }
1925 
1926  // Select Logical(x, ~y) for Logical(x, Xor(y, -1)).
1927  if (rhs.Is<Opmask::kBitwiseXor>() && right_can_cover) {
1928  const WordBinopOp& xor_op = rhs.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
1929  int64_t xor_rhs_val;
1930  if (selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(xor_op.right(), &xor_rhs_val) &&
1931  xor_rhs_val == -1) {
1932  // TODO(all): support shifted operand on right.
1933  selector->Emit(inv_opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
1934  g.UseRegister(logical_op.left()),
1935  g.UseRegister(xor_op.left()));
1936  return;
1937  }
1938  }
1939 
1940  int64_t xor_rhs_val;
1941  if (logical_op.Is<Opmask::kBitwiseXor>() &&
1942  selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(logical_op.right(), &xor_rhs_val) &&
1943  xor_rhs_val == -1) {
1944  const WordBinopOp& xor_op = logical_op.Cast<Opmask::kBitwiseXor>();
1945  bool is32 = rep == WordRepresentation::Word32();
1946  ArchOpcode opcode = is32 ? kArm64Not32 : kArm64Not;
1947  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
1948  g.UseRegister(xor_op.left()));
1949  } else {
1950  VisitBinop(selector, node, rep, opcode, imm_mode);
1951  }
1952 }
1953 
1954 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord32And(OpIndex node) {
1955  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
1956  const WordBinopOp& bitwise_and =
1957  this->Get(node).Cast<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>();
1958  const Operation& lhs = this->Get(bitwise_and.left());
1959  if (int64_t constant_rhs;
1960  lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftRightLogical>() &&
1961  CanCover(node, bitwise_and.left()) &&
1962  MatchSignedIntegralConstant(bitwise_and.right(), &constant_rhs)) {
1963  DCHECK(base::IsInRange(constant_rhs, std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min(),
1964  std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max()));
1965  uint32_t mask = static_cast<uint32_t>(constant_rhs);
1966  uint32_t mask_width = base::bits::CountPopulation(mask);
1967  uint32_t mask_msb = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros32(mask);
1968  if ((mask_width != 0) && (mask_width != 32) &&
1969  (mask_msb + mask_width == 32)) {
1970  // The mask must be contiguous, and occupy the least-significant bits.
1971  DCHECK_EQ(0u, base::bits::CountTrailingZeros32(mask));
1972 
1973  // Select Ubfx for And(Shr(x, imm), mask) where the mask is in the least
1974  // significant bits.
1975  const ShiftOp& lhs_shift = lhs.Cast<Opmask::kWord32ShiftRightLogical>();
1976  if (int64_t constant;
1977  MatchSignedIntegralConstant(lhs_shift.right(), &constant)) {
1978  // Any shift value can match; int32 shifts use `value % 32`.
1979  uint32_t lsb = constant & 0x1F;
1980 
1981  // Ubfx cannot extract bits past the register size, however since
1982  // shifting the original value would have introduced some zeros we can
1983  // still use ubfx with a smaller mask and the remaining bits will be
1984  // zeros.
1985  if (lsb + mask_width > 32) mask_width = 32 - lsb;
1986 
1987  Emit(kArm64Ubfx32, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
1988  g.UseRegister(lhs_shift.left()),
1989  g.UseImmediateOrTemp(lhs_shift.right(), lsb),
1990  g.TempImmediate(mask_width));
1991  return;
1992  }
1993  // Other cases fall through to the normal And operation.
1994  }
1995  }
1996  VisitLogical(this, zone(), node, bitwise_and.rep, kArm64And32,
1997  CanCover(node, bitwise_and.left()),
1998  CanCover(node, bitwise_and.right()), kLogical32Imm);
1999 }
2000 
2001 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord64And(OpIndex node) {
2002  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
2003 
2004  const WordBinopOp& bitwise_and = Get(node).Cast<Opmask::kWord64BitwiseAnd>();
2005  const Operation& lhs = Get(bitwise_and.left());
2006 
2007  if (uint64_t mask;
2008  lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord64ShiftRightLogical>() &&
2009  CanCover(node, bitwise_and.left()) &&
2010  MatchUnsignedIntegralConstant(bitwise_and.right(), &mask)) {
2011  uint64_t mask_width = base::bits::CountPopulation(mask);
2012  uint64_t mask_msb = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros64(mask);
2013  if ((mask_width != 0) && (mask_width != 64) &&
2014  (mask_msb + mask_width == 64)) {
2015  // The mask must be contiguous, and occupy the least-significant bits.
2016  DCHECK_EQ(0u, base::bits::CountTrailingZeros64(mask));
2017 
2018  // Select Ubfx for And(Shr(x, imm), mask) where the mask is in the least
2019  // significant bits.
2020  const ShiftOp& shift = lhs.Cast<ShiftOp>();
2021  if (int64_t shift_by;
2022  MatchSignedIntegralConstant(shift.right(), &shift_by)) {
2023  // Any shift value can match; int64 shifts use `value % 64`.
2024  uint32_t lsb = static_cast<uint32_t>(shift_by & 0x3F);
2025 
2026  // Ubfx cannot extract bits past the register size, however since
2027  // shifting the original value would have introduced some zeros we can
2028  // still use ubfx with a smaller mask and the remaining bits will be
2029  // zeros.
2030  if (lsb + mask_width > 64) mask_width = 64 - lsb;
2031 
2032  Emit(kArm64Ubfx, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(shift.left()),
2033  g.UseImmediateOrTemp(shift.right(), lsb),
2034  g.TempImmediate(static_cast<int32_t>(mask_width)));
2035  return;
2036  }
2037  // Other cases fall through to the normal And operation.
2038  }
2039  }
2040  VisitLogical(this, zone(), node, bitwise_and.rep, kArm64And,
2041  CanCover(node, bitwise_and.left()),
2042  CanCover(node, bitwise_and.right()), kLogical64Imm);
2043 }

2046  const WordBinopOp& op = this->Get(node).template Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2047  VisitLogical(this, zone(), node, op.rep, kArm64Or32,
2048  CanCover(node, op.left()), CanCover(node, op.right()),
2049  kLogical32Imm);
2050 }

2055  CanCover(node, op.right()), kLogical64Imm);
