2071 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord32Shl(OpIndex node) {
2072  const ShiftOp& shift_op = Get(node).Cast<ShiftOp>();
2073  const Operation& lhs = Get(shift_op.left());
2074  if (uint64_t constant_left;
2075  lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>() && CanCover(node, shift_op.left()) &&
2076  MatchUnsignedIntegralConstant(shift_op.right(), &constant_left)) {
2077  uint32_t shift_by = static_cast<uint32_t>(constant_left);
2078  if (base::IsInRange(shift_by, 1, 31)) {
2079  const WordBinopOp& bitwise_and = lhs.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2080  if (uint64_t constant_right;
2081  MatchUnsignedIntegralConstant(bitwise_and.right(), &constant_right)) {
2082  uint32_t mask = static_cast<uint32_t>(constant_right);
2083 
2084  uint32_t mask_width = base::bits::CountPopulation(mask);
2085  uint32_t mask_msb = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros32(mask);
2086  if ((mask_width != 0) && (mask_msb + mask_width == 32)) {
2087  DCHECK_EQ(0u, base::bits::CountTrailingZeros32(mask));
2088  DCHECK_NE(0u, shift_by);
2089  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
2090  if ((shift_by + mask_width) >= 32) {
2091  // If the mask is contiguous and reaches or extends beyond the top
2092  // bit, only the shift is needed.
2093  Emit(kArm64Lsl32, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2094  g.UseRegister(bitwise_and.left()), g.UseImmediate(shift_by));
2095  return;
2096  } else {
2097  // Select Ubfiz for Shl(And(x, mask), imm) where the mask is
2098  // contiguous, and the shift immediate non-zero.
2099  Emit(kArm64Ubfiz32, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2100  g.UseRegister(bitwise_and.left()), g.UseImmediate(shift_by),
2101  g.TempImmediate(mask_width));
2102  return;
2103  }
2104  }
2105  }
2106  }
2107  }
2108  VisitRRO(this, kArm64Lsl32, node, kShift32Imm);
2109 }
2110 
2111 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord64Shl(OpIndex node) {
2112  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
2113  const ShiftOp& shift_op = this->Get(node).template Cast<ShiftOp>();
2114  const Operation& lhs = this->Get(shift_op.left());
2115  const Operation& rhs = this->Get(shift_op.right());
2116  if ((lhs.Is<Opmask::kChangeInt32ToInt64>() ||
2117  lhs.Is<Opmask::kChangeUint32ToUint64>()) &&
2118  rhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32Constant>()) {
2119  int64_t shift_by = rhs.Cast<ConstantOp>().signed_integral();
2120  if (base::IsInRange(shift_by, 32, 63) && CanCover(node, shift_op.left())) {
2121  // There's no need to sign/zero-extend to 64-bit if we shift out the
2122  // upper 32 bits anyway.
2123  Emit(kArm64Lsl, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2124  g.UseRegister(lhs.Cast<ChangeOp>().input()),
2125  g.UseImmediate64(shift_by));
2126  return;
2127  }
2128  }
2129  VisitRRO(this, kArm64Lsl, node, kShift64Imm);
2130 }

2132 void InstructionSelector::VisitStackPointerGreaterThan(
2133  OpIndex node, FlagsContinuation* cont) {
2134  StackCheckKind kind;
2135  OpIndex value;
2136  const auto& op = this->turboshaft_graph()
2137  ->Get(node)
2138  .template Cast<StackPointerGreaterThanOp>();
2139  kind = op.kind;
2140  value = op.stack_limit();
2141  InstructionCode opcode =
2142  kArchStackPointerGreaterThan |
2143  StackCheckField::encode(static_cast<StackCheckKind>(kind));
2144 
2145  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
2146 
2147  // No outputs.
2148  InstructionOperand* const outputs = nullptr;
2149  const int output_count = 0;
2150 
2151  // Applying an offset to this stack check requires a temp register. Offsets
2152  // are only applied to the first stack check. If applying an offset, we must
2153  // ensure the input and temp registers do not alias, thus kUniqueRegister.
2154  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister()};
2155  const int temp_count = (kind == StackCheckKind::kJSFunctionEntry) ? 1 : 0;
2156  const auto register_mode = (kind == StackCheckKind::kJSFunctionEntry)
2157  ? OperandGenerator::kUniqueRegister
2158  : OperandGenerator::kRegister;
2159 
2160  InstructionOperand inputs[] = {g.UseRegisterWithMode(value, register_mode)};
2161  static constexpr int input_count = arraysize(inputs);
2162 
2163  EmitWithContinuation(opcode, output_count, outputs, input_count, inputs,
2164  temp_count, temps, cont);
2165 }

2169 bool TryEmitBitfieldExtract32(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node) {
2170  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
2171  const ShiftOp& shift = selector->Get(node).Cast<ShiftOp>();
2172  const Operation& lhs = selector->Get(shift.left());
2173  if (selector->CanCover(node, shift.left()) &&
2174  lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftLeft>()) {
2175  // Select Ubfx or Sbfx for (x << (K & 0x1F)) OP (K & 0x1F), where
2176  // OP is >>> or >> and (K & 0x1F) != 0.
2177  const ShiftOp& lhs_shift = lhs.Cast<ShiftOp>();
2178  int64_t lhs_shift_by_constant, shift_by_constant;
2179  if (selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(lhs_shift.right(),
2180  &lhs_shift_by_constant) &&
2181  selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(shift.right(),
2182  &shift_by_constant) &&
2183  (lhs_shift_by_constant & 0x1F) != 0 &&
2184  (lhs_shift_by_constant & 0x1F) == (shift_by_constant & 0x1F)) {
2185  DCHECK(shift.Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftRightArithmetic>() ||
2186  shift.Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftRightArithmeticShiftOutZeros>() ||
2187  shift.Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftRightLogical>());
2188 
2189  ArchOpcode opcode = shift.kind == ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightLogical
2190  ? kArm64Ubfx32
2191  : kArm64Sbfx32;
2192 
2193  int right_val = shift_by_constant & 0x1F;
2194  DCHECK_NE(right_val, 0);
2195 
2196  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2197  g.UseRegister(lhs_shift.left()), g.TempImmediate(0),
2198  g.TempImmediate(32 - right_val));
2199  return true;
2200  }
2201  }
2202  return false;
2203 }

2205 } // namespace
2206 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord32Shr(OpIndex node) {
2207  const ShiftOp& shift = Get(node).Cast<ShiftOp>();
2208  const Operation& lhs = Get(shift.left());
2209  uint64_t constant_right;
2210  const bool right_is_constant =
2211  MatchUnsignedIntegralConstant(shift.right(), &constant_right);
2212  if (lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>() && right_is_constant) {
2213  uint32_t lsb = constant_right & 0x1F;
2214  const WordBinopOp& bitwise_and = lhs.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2215  uint32_t constant_bitmask;
2216  if (MatchIntegralWord32Constant(bitwise_and.right(), &constant_bitmask) &&
2217  constant_bitmask != 0) {
2218  // Select Ubfx for Shr(And(x, mask), imm) where the result of the mask is
2219  // shifted into the least-significant bits.
2220  uint32_t mask = (constant_bitmask >> lsb) << lsb;
2221  unsigned mask_width = base::bits::CountPopulation(mask);
2222  unsigned mask_msb = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros32(mask);
2223  if ((mask_msb + mask_width + lsb) == 32) {
2224  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
2225  DCHECK_EQ(lsb, base::bits::CountTrailingZeros32(mask));
2226  Emit(kArm64Ubfx32, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2227  g.UseRegister(bitwise_and.left()),
2228  g.UseImmediateOrTemp(shift.right(), lsb),
2229  g.TempImmediate(mask_width));
2230  return;
2231  }
2232  }
2233  } else if (TryEmitBitfieldExtract32(this, node)) {
2234  return;
2235  }
2236 
2237  if (lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32UnsignedMulOverflownBits>() && right_is_constant &&
2238  CanCover(node, shift.left())) {
2239  // Combine this shift with the multiply and shift that would be generated
2240  // by Uint32MulHigh.
2241  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
2242  const WordBinopOp& mul = lhs.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2243  int shift_by = constant_right & 0x1F;
2244  InstructionOperand const smull_operand = g.TempRegister();
2245  Emit(kArm64Umull, smull_operand, g.UseRegister(mul.left()),
2246  g.UseRegister(mul.right()));
2247  Emit(kArm64Lsr, g.DefineAsRegister(node), smull_operand,
2248  g.TempImmediate(32 + shift_by));
2249  return;
2250  }
2251 
2252  VisitRRO(this, kArm64Lsr32, node, kShift32Imm);
2253 }
2254 
2255 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord64Shr(OpIndex node) {
2256  const ShiftOp& op = Get(node).Cast<ShiftOp>();
2257  const Operation& lhs = Get(op.left());
2258  if (uint64_t constant; lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord64BitwiseAnd>() &&
2259  MatchUnsignedIntegralConstant(op.right(), &constant)) {
2260  uint32_t lsb = constant & 0x3F;
2261  const WordBinopOp& bitwise_and = lhs.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2262  uint64_t constant_and_rhs;
2263  if (MatchIntegralWord64Constant(bitwise_and.right(), &constant_and_rhs) &&
2264  constant_and_rhs != 0) {
2265  // Select Ubfx for Shr(And(x, mask), imm) where the result of the mask is
2266  // shifted into the least-significant bits.
2267  uint64_t mask = static_cast<uint64_t>(constant_and_rhs >> lsb) << lsb;
2268  unsigned mask_width = base::bits::CountPopulation(mask);
2269  unsigned mask_msb = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros64(mask);
2270  if ((mask_msb + mask_width + lsb) == 64) {
2271  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
2272  DCHECK_EQ(lsb, base::bits::CountTrailingZeros64(mask));
2273  Emit(kArm64Ubfx, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2274  g.UseRegister(bitwise_and.left()),
2275  g.UseImmediateOrTemp(op.right(), lsb),
2276  g.TempImmediate(mask_width));
2277  return;
2278  }
2279  }
2280  }
2281  VisitRRO(this, kArm64Lsr, node, kShift64Imm);
2282 }
2283 
2284 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord32Sar(OpIndex node) {
2285  if (TryEmitBitfieldExtract32(this, node)) {
2286  return;
2287  }
2288 
2289  const ShiftOp& shift = Get(node).Cast<ShiftOp>();
2290  const Operation& lhs = Get(shift.left());
2291  uint64_t constant_right;
2292  const bool right_is_constant =
2293  MatchUnsignedIntegralConstant(shift.right(), &constant_right);
2294  if (lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32SignedMulOverflownBits>() && right_is_constant &&
2295  CanCover(node, shift.left())) {
2296  // Combine this shift with the multiply and shift that would be generated
2297  // by Int32MulHigh.
2298  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
2299  const WordBinopOp& mul_overflow = lhs.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2300  int shift_by = constant_right & 0x1F;
2301  InstructionOperand const smull_operand = g.TempRegister();
2302  Emit(kArm64Smull, smull_operand, g.UseRegister(mul_overflow.left()),
2303  g.UseRegister(mul_overflow.right()));
2304  Emit(kArm64Asr, g.DefineAsRegister(node), smull_operand,
2305  g.TempImmediate(32 + shift_by));
2306  return;
2307  }
2308 
2309  if (lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32Add>() && right_is_constant &&
2310  CanCover(node, shift.left())) {
2311  const WordBinopOp& add = Get(shift.left()).Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2312  const Operation& lhs = Get(add.left());
2313  if (lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32SignedMulOverflownBits>() &&
2314  CanCover(shift.left(), add.left())) {
2315  // Combine the shift that would be generated by Int32MulHigh with the add
2316  // on the left of this Sar operation. We do it here, as the result of the
2317  // add potentially has 33 bits, so we have to ensure the result is
2318  // truncated by being the input to this 32-bit Sar operation.
2319  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
2320  const WordBinopOp& mul = lhs.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2321 
2322  InstructionOperand const smull_operand = g.TempRegister();
2323  Emit(kArm64Smull, smull_operand, g.UseRegister(mul.left()),
2324  g.UseRegister(mul.right()));
2325 
2326  InstructionOperand const add_operand = g.TempRegister();
2327  Emit(kArm64Add | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_ASR_I),
2328  add_operand, g.UseRegister(add.right()), smull_operand,
2329  g.TempImmediate(32));
2330 
2331  Emit(kArm64Asr32, g.DefineAsRegister(node), add_operand,
2332  g.UseImmediate(shift.right()));
2333  return;
2334  }
2335  }
2336 
2337  VisitRRO(this, kArm64Asr32, node, kShift32Imm);
2338 }
2339 
2340 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord64Sar(OpIndex node) {
2341  if (TryEmitExtendingLoad(this, node)) return;
2342 
2343  // Select Sbfx(x, imm, 32-imm) for Word64Sar(ChangeInt32ToInt64(x), imm)
2344  // where possible
2345  const ShiftOp& shiftop = Get(node).Cast<ShiftOp>();
2346  const Operation& lhs = Get(shiftop.left());
2347 
2348  int64_t constant_rhs;
2349  if (lhs.Is<Opmask::kChangeInt32ToInt64>() &&
2350  MatchIntegralWord64Constant(shiftop.right(), &constant_rhs) &&
2351  is_uint5(constant_rhs) && CanCover(node, shiftop.left())) {
2352  // Don't select Sbfx here if Asr(Ldrsw(x), imm) can be selected for
2353  // Word64Sar(ChangeInt32ToInt64(Load(x)), imm)
2354  OpIndex input = lhs.Cast<ChangeOp>().input();
2355  if (!Get(input).Is<LoadOp>() || !CanCover(shiftop.left(), input)) {
2356  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
2357  int right = static_cast<int>(constant_rhs);
2358  Emit(kArm64Sbfx, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input),
2359  g.UseImmediate(right), g.UseImmediate(32 - right));
2360  return;
2361  }
2362  }
2363 
2364  VisitRRO(this, kArm64Asr, node, kShift64Imm);
2365 }

2486 void InstructionSelector::VisitInt32Add(OpIndex node) {
2487  const WordBinopOp& add = this->Get(node).Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2488  DCHECK(add.Is<Opmask::kWord32Add>());
2489  V<Word32> left = add.left<Word32>();
2490  V<Word32> right = add.right<Word32>();
2491  // Select Madd(x, y, z) for Add(Mul(x, y), z) or Add(z, Mul(x, y)).
2492  if (TryEmitMultiplyAddInt32(this, node, left, right) ||
2493  TryEmitMultiplyAddInt32(this, node, right, left)) {
2494  return;
2495  }
2496  VisitAddSub(this, node, kArm64Add32, kArm64Sub32);
2497 }

2502  V<Word64> left = add.left<Word64>();
2503  V<Word64> right = add.right<Word64>();

2505  if (TryEmitMultiplyAddInt64(this, node, left, right) ||
2506  TryEmitMultiplyAddInt64(this, node, right, left)) {
2507  return;
2508  }

2510 }

2536 void EmitInt32MulWithOverflow(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
2537  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
2538  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
2539  const OverflowCheckedBinopOp& mul =
2540  selector->Get(node).Cast<OverflowCheckedBinopOp>();
2541  InstructionOperand result = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
2542  InstructionOperand left = g.UseRegister(mul.left());
2543 
2544  int32_t constant_rhs;
2545  if (selector->MatchIntegralWord32Constant(mul.right(), &constant_rhs) &&
2546  base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(constant_rhs)) {
2547  // Sign extend the bottom 32 bits and shift left.
2548  int32_t shift = base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(constant_rhs);
2549  selector->Emit(kArm64Sbfiz, result, left, g.TempImmediate(shift),
2550  g.TempImmediate(32));
2551  } else {
2552  InstructionOperand right = g.UseRegister(mul.right());
2553  selector->Emit(kArm64Smull, result, left, right);
2554  }
2555 
2556  InstructionCode opcode =
2557  kArm64Cmp | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_SXTW);
2558  selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, result, result, cont);
2559 }
2560 
2561 void EmitInt64MulWithOverflow(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
2562  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
2563  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
2564  const OverflowCheckedBinopOp& op =
2565  selector->Cast<OverflowCheckedBinopOp>(node);
2566  InstructionOperand result = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
2567  InstructionOperand left = g.UseRegister(op.left());
2568  InstructionOperand high = g.TempRegister();
2569 
2570  InstructionOperand right = g.UseRegister(op.right());
2571  selector->Emit(kArm64Mul, result, left, right);
2572  selector->Emit(kArm64Smulh, high, left, right);
2573 
2574  // Test whether {high} is a sign-extension of {result}.
2575  InstructionCode opcode =
2576  kArm64Cmp | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_ASR_I);
2577  selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, high, result, g.TempImmediate(63),
2578  cont);
2579 }
2580 
2581 } // namespace
2582 
2583 void InstructionSelector::VisitInt32Mul(OpIndex node) {
2584  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
2585  const WordBinopOp& mul = Get(node).Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2586  DCHECK(mul.Is<Opmask::kWord32Mul>());
2587 
2588  // First, try to reduce the multiplication to addition with left shift.
2589  // x * (2^k + 1) -> x + (x << k)
2590  int32_t shift = LeftShiftForReducedMultiply(this, mul.right());
2591  if (shift > 0) {
2592  Emit(kArm64Add32 | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_LSL_I),
2593  g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(mul.left()),
2594  g.UseRegister(mul.left()), g.TempImmediate(shift));
2595  return;
2596  }
2597 
2598  // Select Mneg(x, y) for Mul(Sub(0, x), y) or Mul(y, Sub(0, x)).
2599  if (TryEmitMultiplyNegateInt32(this, node, mul.left(), mul.right()) ||
2600  TryEmitMultiplyNegateInt32(this, node, mul.right(), mul.left())) {
2601  return;
2602  }
2603 
2604  VisitRRR(this, kArm64Mul32, node);
2605 }
2606 
2607 void InstructionSelector::VisitInt64Mul(OpIndex node) {
2608  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
2609  const WordBinopOp& mul = Get(node).Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2610  DCHECK(mul.Is<Opmask::kWord64Mul>());
2611 
2612  // First, try to reduce the multiplication to addition with left shift.
2613  // x * (2^k + 1) -> x + (x << k)
2614  int32_t shift = LeftShiftForReducedMultiply(this, mul.right());
2615  if (shift > 0) {
2616  Emit(kArm64Add | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Operand2_R_LSL_I),
2617  g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(mul.left()),
2618  g.UseRegister(mul.left()), g.TempImmediate(shift));
2619  return;
2620  }
2621 
2622  // Select Mneg(x, y) for Mul(Sub(0, x), y) or Mul(y, Sub(0, x)).
2623  if (TryEmitMultiplyNegateInt64(this, node, mul.left(), mul.right()) ||
2624  TryEmitMultiplyNegateInt64(this, node, mul.right(), mul.left())) {
2625  return;
2626  }
2627 
2628  VisitRRR(this, kArm64Mul, node);
2629 }

2900 void InstructionSelector::VisitChangeInt32ToInt64(OpIndex node) {
2901  const ChangeOp& change_op = this->Get(node).template Cast<ChangeOp>();
2902  const Operation& input_op = this->Get(change_op.input());
2903  if (input_op.Is<LoadOp>() && CanCover(node, change_op.input())) {
2904  auto load = load_view(change_op.input());
2905  // Generate sign-extending load.
2906  MemoryRepresentation loaded_rep = load.ts_loaded_rep();
2907  MachineRepresentation rep = load.loaded_rep().representation();
2908  InstructionCode opcode = kArchNop;
2909  ImmediateMode immediate_mode = kNoImmediate;
2910  switch (rep) {
2911  case MachineRepresentation::kBit: // Fall through.
2912  case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
2913  opcode = loaded_rep.IsSigned() ? kArm64Ldrsb : kArm64Ldrb;
2914  immediate_mode = kLoadStoreImm8;
2915  break;
2916  case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
2917  opcode = loaded_rep.IsSigned() ? kArm64Ldrsh : kArm64Ldrh;
2918  immediate_mode = kLoadStoreImm16;
2919  break;
2920  case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
2921  case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
2922  // Since BitcastElider may remove nodes of
2923  // IrOpcode::kTruncateInt64ToInt32 and directly use the inputs, values
2924  // with kWord64 can also reach this line.
2925  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned:
2926  case MachineRepresentation::kTagged:
2927  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer:
2928  opcode = kArm64Ldrsw;
2929  immediate_mode = kLoadStoreImm32;
2930  break;
2931  default:
2932  UNREACHABLE();
2933  }
2934  EmitLoad(this, change_op.input(), opcode, immediate_mode, loaded_rep, node);
2935  return;
2936  }
2937  if ((input_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftRightArithmetic>() ||
2938  input_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftRightArithmeticShiftOutZeros>()) &&
2939  CanCover(node, change_op.input())) {
2940  const ShiftOp& sar = input_op.Cast<ShiftOp>();
2941  if (int64_t constant; MatchSignedIntegralConstant(sar.right(), &constant)) {
2942  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
2943  // Mask the shift amount, to keep the same semantics as Word32Sar.
2944  int right = constant & 0x1F;
2945  Emit(kArm64Sbfx, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(sar.left()),
2946  g.TempImmediate(right), g.TempImmediate(32 - right));
2947  return;
2948  }
2949  }
2950  VisitRR(this, kArm64Sxtw, node);
2951 }
2952 
2953 bool InstructionSelector::ZeroExtendsWord32ToWord64NoPhis(OpIndex node) {
2954  DCHECK(!this->Get(node).Is<PhiOp>());
2955  const Operation& op = this->Get(node);
2956  // 32-bit operations will write their result in a W register (implicitly
2957  // clearing the top 32-bit of the corresponding X register) so the
2958  // zero-extension is a no-op.
2959  switch (op.opcode) {
2960  case Opcode::kWordBinop:
2961  return op.Cast<WordBinopOp>().rep == WordRepresentation::Word32();
2962  case Opcode::kShift:
2963  return op.Cast<ShiftOp>().rep == WordRepresentation::Word32();
2964  case Opcode::kComparison:
2965  return op.Cast<ComparisonOp>().rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
2966  case Opcode::kOverflowCheckedBinop:
2967  return op.Cast<OverflowCheckedBinopOp>().rep ==
2968  WordRepresentation::Word32();
2969  case Opcode::kProjection:
2970  return ZeroExtendsWord32ToWord64NoPhis(op.Cast<ProjectionOp>().input());
2971  case Opcode::kLoad: {
2972  RegisterRepresentation rep =
2973  op.Cast<LoadOp>().loaded_rep.ToRegisterRepresentation();
2974  return rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
2975  }
2976  default:
2977  return false;
2978  }
2979 }

3027 void InstructionSelector::EmitPrepareArguments(
3028  ZoneVector<PushParameter>* arguments, const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
3029  OpIndex node) {
3030  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
3031 
3032  // `arguments` includes alignment "holes". This means that slots bigger than
3033  // kSystemPointerSize, e.g. Simd128, will span across multiple arguments.
3034  int claim_count = static_cast<int>(arguments->size());
3035  bool needs_padding = claim_count % 2 != 0;
3036  int slot = claim_count - 1;
3037  claim_count = RoundUp(claim_count, 2);
3038  // Bump the stack pointer.
3039  if (claim_count > 0) {
3040  // TODO(titzer): claim and poke probably take small immediates.
3041  // TODO(titzer): it would be better to bump the sp here only
3042  // and emit paired stores with increment for non c frames.
3043  Emit(kArm64Claim, g.NoOutput(), g.TempImmediate(claim_count));
3044 
3045  if (needs_padding) {
3046  Emit(kArm64Poke, g.NoOutput(), g.UseImmediate(0),
3047  g.TempImmediate(claim_count - 1));
3048  }
3049  }
3050 
3051  // Poke the arguments into the stack.
3052  while (slot >= 0) {
3053  PushParameter input0 = (*arguments)[slot];
3054  // Skip holes in the param array. These represent both extra slots for
3055  // multi-slot values and padding slots for alignment.
3056  if (!input0.node.valid()) {
3057  slot--;
3058  continue;
3059  }
3060  PushParameter input1 = slot > 0 ? (*arguments)[slot - 1] : PushParameter();
3061  // Emit a poke-pair if consecutive parameters have the same type.
3062  // TODO(arm): Support consecutive Simd128 parameters.
3063  if (input1.node.valid() &&
3064  input0.location.GetType() == input1.location.GetType()) {
3065  Emit(kArm64PokePair, g.NoOutput(), g.UseRegister(input0.node),
3066  g.UseRegister(input1.node), g.TempImmediate(slot));
3067  slot -= 2;
3068  } else {
3069  Emit(kArm64Poke, g.NoOutput(), g.UseRegister(input0.node),
3070  g.TempImmediate(slot));
3071  slot--;
3072  }
3073  }
3074 }
3075 
3076 void InstructionSelector::EmitPrepareResults(
3077  ZoneVector<PushParameter>* results, const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
3078  OpIndex node) {
3079  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
3080 
3081  for (PushParameter output : *results) {
3082  if (!output.location.IsCallerFrameSlot()) continue;
3083  // Skip any alignment holes in nodes.
3084  if (output.node.valid()) {
3085  DCHECK(!call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall());
3086 
3087  if (output.location.GetType() == MachineType::Float32()) {
3088  MarkAsFloat32(output.node);
3089  } else if (output.location.GetType() == MachineType::Float64()) {
3090  MarkAsFloat64(output.node);
3091  } else if (output.location.GetType() == MachineType::Simd128()) {
3092  MarkAsSimd128(output.node);
3093  }
3094 
3095  int offset = call_descriptor->GetOffsetToReturns();
3096  int reverse_slot = -output.location.GetLocation() - offset;
3097  Emit(kArm64Peek, g.DefineAsRegister(output.node),
3098  g.UseImmediate(reverse_slot));
3099  }
3100  }
3101 }

3107 // Shared routine for multiple compare operations.
3108 void VisitCompare(InstructionSelector* selector, InstructionCode opcode,
3109  InstructionOperand left, InstructionOperand right,
3110  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3111  if (cont->IsSelect()) {
3112  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3113  InstructionOperand inputs[] = {
3114  left, right, g.UseRegisterOrImmediateZero(cont->true_value()),
3115  g.UseRegisterOrImmediateZero(cont->false_value())};
3116  selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, 0, nullptr, 4, inputs, cont);
3117  } else {
3118  selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, left, right, cont);
3119  }
3120 }
3121 
3122 // This function checks whether we can convert:
3123 // ((a <op> b) cmp 0), b.<cond>
3124 // to:
3125 // (a <ops> b), b.<cond'>
3126 // where <ops> is the flag setting version of <op>.
3127 // We only generate conditions <cond'> that are a combination of the N
3128 // and Z flags. This avoids the need to make this function dependent on
3129 // the flag-setting operation.
3130 bool CanUseFlagSettingBinop(FlagsCondition cond) {
3131  switch (cond) {
3132  case kEqual:
3133  case kNotEqual:
3134  case kSignedLessThan:
3135  case kSignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
3136  case kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual: // x <= 0 -> x == 0
3137  case kUnsignedGreaterThan: // x > 0 -> x != 0
3138  return true;
3139  default:
3140  return false;
3141  }
3142 }
3143 
3144 // Map <cond> to <cond'> so that the following transformation is possible:
3145 // ((a <op> b) cmp 0), b.<cond>
3146 // to:
3147 // (a <ops> b), b.<cond'>
3148 // where <ops> is the flag setting version of <op>.
3149 FlagsCondition MapForFlagSettingBinop(FlagsCondition cond) {
3150  DCHECK(CanUseFlagSettingBinop(cond));
3151  switch (cond) {
3152  case kEqual:
3153  case kNotEqual:
3154  return cond;
3155  case kSignedLessThan:
3156  return kNegative;
3157  case kSignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
3158  return kPositiveOrZero;
3159  case kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual: // x <= 0 -> x == 0
3160  return kEqual;
3161  case kUnsignedGreaterThan: // x > 0 -> x != 0
3162  return kNotEqual;
3163  default:
3164  UNREACHABLE();
3165  }
3166 }
3167 
3168 // This function checks if we can perform the transformation:
3169 // ((a <op> b) cmp 0), b.<cond>
3170 // to:
3171 // (a <ops> b), b.<cond'>
3172 // where <ops> is the flag setting version of <op>, and if so,
3173 // updates {node}, {opcode} and {cont} accordingly.
3174 void MaybeReplaceCmpZeroWithFlagSettingBinop(InstructionSelector* selector,
3175  OpIndex* node, OpIndex binop,
3176  ArchOpcode* opcode,
3177  FlagsCondition cond,
3178  FlagsContinuation* cont,
3179  ImmediateMode* immediate_mode) {
3180  ArchOpcode binop_opcode;
3181  ArchOpcode no_output_opcode;
3182  ImmediateMode binop_immediate_mode;
3183  const Operation& op = selector->Get(binop);
3184  if (op.Is<Opmask::kWord32Add>()) {
3185  binop_opcode = kArm64Add32;
3186  no_output_opcode = kArm64Cmn32;
3187  binop_immediate_mode = kArithmeticImm;
3188  } else if (op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>()) {
3189  binop_opcode = kArm64And32;
3190  no_output_opcode = kArm64Tst32;
3191  binop_immediate_mode = kLogical32Imm;
3192  } else {
3193  UNREACHABLE();
3194  }
3195  if (selector->CanCover(*node, binop)) {
3196  // The comparison is the only user of the add or and, so we can generate
3197  // a cmn or tst instead.
3198  cont->Overwrite(MapForFlagSettingBinop(cond));
3199  *opcode = no_output_opcode;
3200  *node = binop;
3201  *immediate_mode = binop_immediate_mode;
3202  } else if (selector->IsOnlyUserOfNodeInSameBlock(*node, binop)) {
3203  // We can also handle the case where the add and the compare are in the
3204  // same basic block, and the compare is the only use of add in this basic
3205  // block (the add has users in other basic blocks).
3206  cont->Overwrite(MapForFlagSettingBinop(cond));
3207  *opcode = binop_opcode;
3208  *node = binop;
3209  *immediate_mode = binop_immediate_mode;
3210  }
3211 }
3212 
3213 // Map {cond} to kEqual or kNotEqual, so that we can select
3214 // either TBZ or TBNZ when generating code for:
3215 // (x cmp 0), b.{cond}
3216 FlagsCondition MapForTbz(FlagsCondition cond) {
3217  switch (cond) {
3218  case kSignedLessThan: // generate TBNZ
3219  return kNotEqual;
3220  case kSignedGreaterThanOrEqual: // generate TBZ
3221  return kEqual;
3222  default:
3223  UNREACHABLE();
3224  }
3225 }
3226 
3227 // Map {cond} to kEqual or kNotEqual, so that we can select
3228 // either CBZ or CBNZ when generating code for:
3229 // (x cmp 0), b.{cond}
3230 FlagsCondition MapForCbz(FlagsCondition cond) {
3231  switch (cond) {
3232  case kEqual: // generate CBZ
3233  case kNotEqual: // generate CBNZ
3234  return cond;
3235  case kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual: // generate CBZ
3236  return kEqual;
3237  case kUnsignedGreaterThan: // generate CBNZ
3238  return kNotEqual;
3239  default:
3240  UNREACHABLE();
3241  }
3242 }
3243 
3244 void EmitBranchOrDeoptimize(InstructionSelector* selector,
3245  InstructionCode opcode, InstructionOperand value,
3246  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3247  DCHECK(cont->IsBranch() || cont->IsDeoptimize());
3248  if ((cont->IsBranch() && cont->hint() != BranchHint::kNone) ||
3249  cont->IsDeoptimize()) {
3250  opcode |= BranchHintField::encode(true);
3251  }
3252  selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, value, cont);
3253 }

3255 template <int N>
3256 struct CbzOrTbzMatchTrait {};
3257 
3258 template <>
3259 struct CbzOrTbzMatchTrait<32> {
3260  using IntegralType = uint32_t;
3261  using BinopMatcher = Int32BinopMatcher;
3262  static constexpr ArchOpcode kTestAndBranchOpcode = kArm64TestAndBranch32;
3263  static constexpr ArchOpcode kCompareAndBranchOpcode =
3264  kArm64CompareAndBranch32;
3265  static constexpr unsigned kSignBit = kWSignBit;
3266 };
3267 
3268 template <>
3269 struct CbzOrTbzMatchTrait<64> {
3270  using IntegralType = uint64_t;
3271  using BinopMatcher = Int64BinopMatcher;
3272  static constexpr ArchOpcode kTestAndBranchOpcode = kArm64TestAndBranch;
3273  static constexpr ArchOpcode kCompareAndBranchOpcode = kArm64CompareAndBranch;
3274  static constexpr unsigned kSignBit = kXSignBit;
3275 };
3276 
3277 // Try to emit TBZ, TBNZ, CBZ or CBNZ for certain comparisons of {node}
3278 // against {value}, depending on the condition.
3279 template <int N>
3280 bool TryEmitCbzOrTbz(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3281  typename CbzOrTbzMatchTrait<N>::IntegralType value,
3282  OpIndex user, FlagsCondition cond,
3283  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3284  // Only handle branches and deoptimisations.
3285  if (!cont->IsBranch() && !cont->IsDeoptimize()) return false;
3286 
3287  switch (cond) {
3288  case kSignedLessThan:
3289  case kSignedGreaterThanOrEqual: {
3290  // Here we handle sign tests, aka. comparisons with zero.
3291  if (value != 0) return false;
3292  // We don't generate TBZ/TBNZ for deoptimisations, as they have a
3293  // shorter range than conditional branches and generating them for
3294  // deoptimisations results in more veneers.
3295  if (cont->IsDeoptimize()) return false;
3296  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3297  cont->Overwrite(MapForTbz(cond));
3298 
3299  if (N == 32) {
3300  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
3301  if (op.Is<Opmask::kFloat64ExtractHighWord32>() &&
3302  selector->CanCover(user, node)) {
3303  // SignedLessThan(Float64ExtractHighWord32(x), 0) and
3304  // SignedGreaterThanOrEqual(Float64ExtractHighWord32(x), 0)
3305  // essentially check the sign bit of a 64-bit floating point value.
3306  InstructionOperand temp = g.TempRegister();
3307  selector->Emit(kArm64U64MoveFloat64, temp,
3308  g.UseRegister(op.input(0)));
3309  selector->EmitWithContinuation(kArm64TestAndBranch, temp,
3310  g.TempImmediate(kDSignBit), cont);
3311  return true;
3312  }
3313  }
3314 
3315  selector->EmitWithContinuation(
3316  CbzOrTbzMatchTrait<N>::kTestAndBranchOpcode, g.UseRegister(node),
3317  g.TempImmediate(CbzOrTbzMatchTrait<N>::kSignBit), cont);
3318  return true;
3319  }
3320  case kEqual:
3321  case kNotEqual: {
3322  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
3323  if (const WordBinopOp* bitwise_and = op.TryCast<Opmask::kBitwiseAnd>()) {
3324  // Emit a tbz/tbnz if we are comparing with a single-bit mask:
3325  // Branch(WordEqual(WordAnd(x, 1 << N), 1 << N), true, false)
3326  uint64_t actual_value;
3327  if (cont->IsBranch() && base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(value) &&
3328  selector->MatchUnsignedIntegralConstant(bitwise_and->right(),
3329  &actual_value) &&
3330  actual_value == value && selector->CanCover(user, node)) {
3331  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3332  // In the code generator, Equal refers to a bit being cleared. We
3333  // want the opposite here so negate the condition.
3334  cont->Negate();
3335  selector->EmitWithContinuation(
3336  CbzOrTbzMatchTrait<N>::kTestAndBranchOpcode,
3337  g.UseRegister(bitwise_and->left()),
3338  g.TempImmediate(base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(value)), cont);
3339  return true;
3340  }
3341  }
3342  [[fallthrough]];
3343  }
3344  case kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual:
3345  case kUnsignedGreaterThan: {
3346  if (value != 0) return false;
3347  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3348  cont->Overwrite(MapForCbz(cond));
3349  EmitBranchOrDeoptimize(selector,
3350  CbzOrTbzMatchTrait<N>::kCompareAndBranchOpcode,
3351  g.UseRegister(node), cont);
3352  return true;
3353  }
3354  default:
3355  return false;
3356  }
3357 }
3358 
3359 // Shared routine for multiple word compare operations.
3360 void VisitWordCompare(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3361  InstructionCode opcode, FlagsContinuation* cont,
3362  ImmediateMode immediate_mode) {
3363  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3364  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
3365  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2);
3366  auto left = op.input(0);
3367  auto right = op.input(1);
3368 
3369  // If one of the two inputs is an immediate, make sure it's on the right.
3370  if (!g.CanBeImmediate(right, immediate_mode) &&
3371  g.CanBeImmediate(left, immediate_mode)) {
3372  cont->Commute();
3373  std::swap(left, right);
3374  }
3375 
3376  int64_t constant;
3377  if (opcode == kArm64Cmp &&
3378  selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(right, &constant)) {
3379  if (TryEmitCbzOrTbz<64>(selector, left, constant, node, cont->condition(),
3380  cont)) {
3381  return;
3382  }
3383  }
3384 
3385  VisitCompare(selector, opcode, g.UseRegister(left),
3386  g.UseOperand(right, immediate_mode), cont);
3387 }
3388 
3389 void VisitWord32Compare(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3390  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3391  const Operation& compare = selector->Get(node);
3392  DCHECK_GE(compare.input_count, 2);
3393  OpIndex lhs = compare.input(0);
3394  OpIndex rhs = compare.input(1);
3395  FlagsCondition cond = cont->condition();
3396 
3397  if (uint64_t constant;
3398  selector->MatchUnsignedIntegralConstant(rhs, &constant) &&
3399  TryEmitCbzOrTbz<32>(selector, lhs, static_cast<uint32_t>(constant), node,
3400  cond, cont)) {
3401  return;
3402  }
3403  if (uint64_t constant;
3404  selector->MatchUnsignedIntegralConstant(lhs, &constant) &&
3405  TryEmitCbzOrTbz<32>(selector, rhs, static_cast<uint32_t>(constant), node,
3406  CommuteFlagsCondition(cond), cont)) {
3407  return;
3408  }
3409 
3410  const Operation& left = selector->Get(lhs);
3411  const Operation& right = selector->Get(rhs);
3412  ArchOpcode opcode = kArm64Cmp32;
3413  ImmediateMode immediate_mode = kArithmeticImm;
3414 
3415  if (selector->MatchIntegralZero(rhs) &&
3416  (left.Is<Opmask::kWord32Add>() || left.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>())) {
3417  // Emit flag setting add/and instructions for comparisons against zero.
3418  if (CanUseFlagSettingBinop(cond)) {
3419  MaybeReplaceCmpZeroWithFlagSettingBinop(selector, &node, lhs, &opcode,
3420  cond, cont, &immediate_mode);
3421  }
3422  } else if (selector->MatchIntegralZero(lhs) &&
3423  (right.Is<Opmask::kWord32Add>() ||
3424  right.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>())) {
3425  // Same as above, but we need to commute the condition before we
3426  // continue with the rest of the checks.
3427  FlagsCondition commuted_cond = CommuteFlagsCondition(cond);
3428  if (CanUseFlagSettingBinop(commuted_cond)) {
3429  MaybeReplaceCmpZeroWithFlagSettingBinop(
3430  selector, &node, rhs, &opcode, commuted_cond, cont, &immediate_mode);
3431  }
3432  } else if (right.Is<Opmask::kWord32Sub>() &&
3433  (cond == kEqual || cond == kNotEqual)) {
3434  const WordBinopOp& sub = right.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
3435  if (selector->MatchIntegralZero(sub.left())) {
3436  // For a given compare(x, 0 - y) where compare is kEqual or kNotEqual,
3437  // it can be expressed as cmn(x, y).
3438  opcode = kArm64Cmn32;
3439  VisitBinopImpl(selector, node, lhs, sub.right(),
3440  RegisterRepresentation::Word32(), opcode, immediate_mode,
3441  cont);
3442  return;
3443  }
3444  }
3445  VisitBinop(selector, node, RegisterRepresentation::Word32(), opcode,
3446  immediate_mode, cont);
3447 }

3451  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3452  VisitCompare(selector, opcode, g.UseRegister(node), g.UseRegister(node),
3453  cont);

3466 struct TestAndBranchMatcherTurboshaft {
3467  TestAndBranchMatcherTurboshaft(InstructionSelector* selector,
3468  const WordBinopOp& binop)
3469  : selector_(selector), binop_(binop) {
3470  Initialize();
3471  }
3472 
3473  bool Matches() const { return matches_; }
3474 
3475  unsigned bit() const {
3476  DCHECK(Matches());
3477  return bit_;
3478  }
3479 
3480  private:
3481  void Initialize() {
3482  if (binop_.kind != WordBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseAnd) return;
3483  uint64_t value{0};
3484  if (!selector_->MatchUnsignedIntegralConstant(binop_.right(), &value) ||
3485  !base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(value)) {
3486  return;
3487  }
3488  // All preconditions for TBZ/TBNZ matched.
3489  matches_ = true;
3490  bit_ = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(value);
3491  }
3492 
3493  InstructionSelector* selector_;
3494  const WordBinopOp& binop_;
3495  bool matches_ = false;
3496  unsigned bit_ = 0;
3497 };

3499 // Shared routine for multiple float32 compare operations.
3500 void VisitFloat32Compare(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3501  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3502  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3503  const ComparisonOp& op = selector->Get(node).template Cast<ComparisonOp>();
3504  OpIndex left = op.left();
3505  OpIndex right = op.right();
3506  if (selector->MatchZero(right)) {
3507  VisitCompare(selector, kArm64Float32Cmp, g.UseRegister(left),
3508  g.UseImmediate(right), cont);
3509  } else if (selector->MatchZero(left)) {
3510  cont->Commute();
3511  VisitCompare(selector, kArm64Float32Cmp, g.UseRegister(right),
3512  g.UseImmediate(left), cont);
3513  } else {
3514  VisitCompare(selector, kArm64Float32Cmp, g.UseRegister(left),
3515  g.UseRegister(right), cont);
3516  }
3517 }
3518 
3519 // Shared routine for multiple float64 compare operations.
3520 void VisitFloat64Compare(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3521  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3522  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3523  const Operation& compare = selector->Get(node);
3524  DCHECK(compare.Is<ComparisonOp>());
3525  OpIndex lhs = compare.input(0);
3526  OpIndex rhs = compare.input(1);
3527  if (selector->MatchZero(rhs)) {
3528  VisitCompare(selector, kArm64Float64Cmp, g.UseRegister(lhs),
3529  g.UseImmediate(rhs), cont);
3530  } else if (selector->MatchZero(lhs)) {
3531  cont->Commute();
3532  VisitCompare(selector, kArm64Float64Cmp, g.UseRegister(rhs),
3533  g.UseImmediate(lhs), cont);
3534  } else {
3535  VisitCompare(selector, kArm64Float64Cmp, g.UseRegister(lhs),
3536  g.UseRegister(rhs), cont);
3537  }
3538 }

3540 void VisitAtomicExchange(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3541  ArchOpcode opcode, AtomicWidth width,
3542  MemoryAccessKind access_kind) {
3543  using OpIndex = OpIndex;
3544  const AtomicRMWOp& atomic_op = selector->Cast<AtomicRMWOp>(node);
3545  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3546  OpIndex base = atomic_op.base();
3547  OpIndex index = atomic_op.index();
3548  OpIndex value = atomic_op.value();
3549  InstructionOperand inputs[3];
3550  if (opcode == kAtomicExchangeWithWriteBarrier) {
3551  // All inputs registers need to be non-aliasing with the temp registers as
3552  // the original inputs are still needed when emitting the write barrier.
3553  inputs[0] = g.UseUniqueRegister(base);
3554  inputs[1] = g.UseUniqueRegister(index);
3555  inputs[2] = g.UseUniqueRegister(value);
3556  } else {
3557  inputs[0] = g.UseRegister(base);
3558  inputs[1] = g.UseRegister(index);
3559  inputs[2] = g.UseUniqueRegister(value);
3560  }
3561  InstructionOperand outputs[] = {g.DefineAsRegister(node)};
3562  InstructionCode code = opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRR) |
3563  AtomicWidthField::encode(width);
3564  if (access_kind == MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler) {
3565  code |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
3566  }
3567  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) {
3568  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister()};
3569  selector->Emit(code, arraysize(outputs), outputs, arraysize(inputs), inputs,
3570  arraysize(temps), temps);
3571  } else {
3572  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister(), g.TempRegister()};
3573  selector->Emit(code, arraysize(outputs), outputs, arraysize(inputs), inputs,
3574  arraysize(temps), temps);
3575  }
3576 }
3577 
3578 void VisitAtomicCompareExchange(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3579  ArchOpcode opcode, AtomicWidth width,
3580  MemoryAccessKind access_kind) {
3581  using OpIndex = OpIndex;
3582  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3583  const AtomicRMWOp& atomic_op = selector->Cast<AtomicRMWOp>(node);
3584  OpIndex base = atomic_op.base();
3585  OpIndex index = atomic_op.index();
3586  OpIndex old_value = atomic_op.expected().value();
3587  OpIndex new_value = atomic_op.value();
3588  InstructionOperand inputs[] = {g.UseRegister(base), g.UseRegister(index),
3589  g.UseUniqueRegister(old_value),
3590  g.UseUniqueRegister(new_value)};
3591  InstructionOperand outputs[1];
3592  InstructionCode code = opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRR) |
3593  AtomicWidthField::encode(width);
3594  if (access_kind == MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler) {
3595  code |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
3596  }
3597  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) {
3598  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister()};
3599  outputs[0] = g.DefineSameAsInput(node, 2);
3600  selector->Emit(code, arraysize(outputs), outputs, arraysize(inputs), inputs,
3601  arraysize(temps), temps);
3602  } else {
3603  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister(), g.TempRegister()};
3604  outputs[0] = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
3605  selector->Emit(code, arraysize(outputs), outputs, arraysize(inputs), inputs,
3606  arraysize(temps), temps);
3607  }
3608 }

3610 void VisitAtomicLoad(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3611  AtomicWidth width) {
3612  using OpIndex = OpIndex;
3613  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3614  auto load = selector->load_view(node);
3615  OpIndex base = load.base();
3616  OpIndex index = load.index();
3617  InstructionOperand inputs[] = {g.UseRegister(base), g.UseRegister(index)};
3618  InstructionOperand outputs[] = {g.DefineAsRegister(node)};
3619  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister()};
3620 
3621  // The memory order is ignored as both acquire and sequentially consistent
3622  // loads can emit LDAR.
3623  // https://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~pes20/cpp/cpp0xmappings.html
3624  LoadRepresentation load_rep = load.loaded_rep();
3625  InstructionCode code;
3626  switch (load_rep.representation()) {
3627  case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
3628  DCHECK_IMPLIES(load_rep.IsSigned(), width == AtomicWidth::kWord32);
3629  code = load_rep.IsSigned() ? kAtomicLoadInt8 : kAtomicLoadUint8;
3630  break;
3631  case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
3632  DCHECK_IMPLIES(load_rep.IsSigned(), width == AtomicWidth::kWord32);
3633  code = load_rep.IsSigned() ? kAtomicLoadInt16 : kAtomicLoadUint16;
3634  break;
3635  case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
3636  code = kAtomicLoadWord32;
3637  break;
3638  case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
3639  code = kArm64Word64AtomicLoadUint64;
3640  break;
3641 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
3642  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned:
3643  code = kArm64LdarDecompressTaggedSigned;
3644  break;
3645  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer:
3646  code = kArm64LdarDecompressTagged;
3647  break;
3648  case MachineRepresentation::kTagged:
3649  code = kArm64LdarDecompressTagged;
3650  break;
3651 #else
3652  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned: // Fall through.
3653  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer: // Fall through.
3654  case MachineRepresentation::kTagged:
3655  if (kTaggedSize == 8) {
3656  code = kArm64Word64AtomicLoadUint64;
3657  } else {
3658  code = kAtomicLoadWord32;
3659  }
3660  break;
3661 #endif
3662  case MachineRepresentation::kCompressedPointer: // Fall through.
3663  case MachineRepresentation::kCompressed:
3664  DCHECK(COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL);
3665  code = kAtomicLoadWord32;
3666  break;
3667  default:
3668  UNREACHABLE();
3669  }
3670 
3671  bool traps_on_null;
3672  if (load.is_protected(&traps_on_null)) {
3673  code |= AccessModeField::encode(traps_on_null
3674  ? kMemoryAccessProtectedNullDereference
3675  : kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
3676  }
3677 
3678  code |=
3679  AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRR) | AtomicWidthField::encode(width);
3680  selector->Emit(code, arraysize(outputs), outputs, arraysize(inputs), inputs,
3681  arraysize(temps), temps);
3682 }
3683 
3684 AtomicStoreParameters AtomicStoreParametersOf(InstructionSelector* selector,
3685  OpIndex node) {
3686  auto store = selector->store_view(node);
3687  return AtomicStoreParameters(store.stored_rep().representation(),
3688  store.stored_rep().write_barrier_kind(),
3689  store.memory_order().value(),
3690  store.access_kind());
3691 }
3692 
3693 void VisitAtomicStore(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3694  AtomicWidth width) {
3695  using OpIndex = OpIndex;
3696  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3697  auto store = selector->store_view(node);
3698  OpIndex base = store.base();
3699  OpIndex index = store.index().value();
3700  OpIndex value = store.value();
3701  DCHECK_EQ(store.displacement(), 0);
3702 
3703  // The memory order is ignored as both release and sequentially consistent
3704  // stores can emit STLR.
3705  // https://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~pes20/cpp/cpp0xmappings.html
3706  AtomicStoreParameters store_params = AtomicStoreParametersOf(selector, node);
3707  WriteBarrierKind write_barrier_kind = store_params.write_barrier_kind();
3708  MachineRepresentation rep = store_params.representation();
3709 
3710  if (v8_flags.enable_unconditional_write_barriers &&
3711  CanBeTaggedOrCompressedPointer(rep)) {
3712  write_barrier_kind = kFullWriteBarrier;
3713  }
3714 
3715  InstructionOperand inputs[] = {g.UseUniqueRegister(base),
3716  g.UseUniqueRegister(index),
3717  g.UseUniqueRegister(value)};
3718  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister()};
3719  InstructionCode code;
3720 
3721  if (write_barrier_kind != kNoWriteBarrier &&
3722  !v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) {
3723  DCHECK(CanBeTaggedOrCompressedPointer(rep));
3724  DCHECK_EQ(AtomicWidthSize(width), kTaggedSize);
3725 
3726  RecordWriteMode record_write_mode =
3727  WriteBarrierKindToRecordWriteMode(write_barrier_kind);
3728  code = kArchAtomicStoreWithWriteBarrier;
3729  code |= RecordWriteModeField::encode(record_write_mode);
3730  } else {
3731  switch (rep) {
3732  case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
3733  code = kAtomicStoreWord8;
3734  break;
3735  case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
3736  code = kAtomicStoreWord16;
3737  break;
3738  case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
3739  code = kAtomicStoreWord32;
3740  break;
3741  case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
3742  DCHECK_EQ(width, AtomicWidth::kWord64);
3743  code = kArm64Word64AtomicStoreWord64;
3744  break;
3745  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned: // Fall through.
3746  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer: // Fall through.
3747  case MachineRepresentation::kTagged:
3748  DCHECK_EQ(AtomicWidthSize(width), kTaggedSize);
3749  code = kArm64StlrCompressTagged;
3750  break;
3751  case MachineRepresentation::kCompressedPointer: // Fall through.
3752  case MachineRepresentation::kCompressed:
3753  CHECK(COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL);
3754  DCHECK_EQ(width, AtomicWidth::kWord32);
3755  code = kArm64StlrCompressTagged;
3756  break;
3757  default:
3758  UNREACHABLE();
3759  }
3760  code |= AtomicWidthField::encode(width);
3761  }
3762 
3763  if (store.is_store_trap_on_null()) {
3764  code |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedNullDereference);
3765  } else if (store_params.kind() == MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler) {
3766  code |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
3767  }
3768 
3769  code |= AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRR);
3770  selector->Emit(code, 0, nullptr, arraysize(inputs), inputs, arraysize(temps),
3771  temps);
3772 }
3773 
3774 void VisitAtomicBinop(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3775  ArchOpcode opcode, AtomicWidth width,
3776  MemoryAccessKind access_kind) {
3777  using OpIndex = OpIndex;
3778  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3779  const AtomicRMWOp& atomic_op = selector->Cast<AtomicRMWOp>(node);
3780  OpIndex base = atomic_op.base();
3781  OpIndex index = atomic_op.index();
3782  OpIndex value = atomic_op.value();
3783  AddressingMode addressing_mode = kMode_MRR;
3784  InstructionOperand inputs[] = {g.UseRegister(base), g.UseRegister(index),
3785  g.UseUniqueRegister(value)};
3786  InstructionOperand outputs[] = {g.DefineAsRegister(node)};
3787  InstructionCode code = opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode) |
3788  AtomicWidthField::encode(width);
3789  if (access_kind == MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler) {
3790  code |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
3791  }
3792 
3793  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) {
3794  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister()};
3795  selector->Emit(code, arraysize(outputs), outputs, arraysize(inputs), inputs,
3796  arraysize(temps), temps);
3797  } else {
3798  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister(), g.TempRegister(),
3799  g.TempRegister()};
3800  selector->Emit(code, arraysize(outputs), outputs, arraysize(inputs), inputs,
3801  arraysize(temps), temps);
3802  }
3803 }

3806 
3807 void InstructionSelector::VisitWordCompareZero(OpIndex user, OpIndex value,
3808  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3809  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
3810  // Try to combine with comparisons against 0 by simply inverting the branch.
3811  ConsumeEqualZero(&user, &value, cont);
3812 
3813  // Remove Word64->Word32 truncation.
3814  if (V<Word64> value64;
3815  MatchTruncateWord64ToWord32(value, &value64) && CanCover(user, value)) {
3816  user = value;
3817  value = value64;
3818  }
3819 
3820  // Try to match bit checks to create TBZ/TBNZ instructions.
3821  // Unlike the switch below, CanCover check is not needed here.
3822  // If there are several uses of the given operation, we will generate a TBZ
3823  // instruction for each. This is useful even if there are other uses of the
3824  // arithmetic result, because it moves dependencies further back.
3825  const Operation& value_op = Get(value);
3826 
3827  if (cont->IsBranch()) {
3828  if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord64Equal>()) {
3829  const ComparisonOp& equal = value_op.Cast<ComparisonOp>();
3830  if (MatchIntegralZero(equal.right())) {
3831  const WordBinopOp* left_binop =
3832  Get(equal.left()).TryCast<WordBinopOp>();
3833  if (left_binop) {
3834  TestAndBranchMatcherTurboshaft matcher(this, *left_binop);
3835  if (matcher.Matches()) {
3836  // If the mask has only one bit set, we can use tbz/tbnz.
3837  DCHECK((cont->condition() == kEqual) ||
3838  (cont->condition() == kNotEqual));
3839  Arm64OperandGenerator gen(this);
3840  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
3841  EmitWithContinuation(kArm64TestAndBranch,
3842  gen.UseRegister(left_binop->left()),
3843  gen.TempImmediate(matcher.bit()), cont);
3844  return;
3845  }
3846  }
3847  }
3848  }
3849 
3850  if (const WordBinopOp* value_binop = value_op.TryCast<WordBinopOp>()) {
3851  TestAndBranchMatcherTurboshaft matcher(this, *value_binop);
3852  if (matcher.Matches()) {
3853  // If the mask has only one bit set, we can use tbz/tbnz.
3854  DCHECK((cont->condition() == kEqual) ||
3855  (cont->condition() == kNotEqual));
3856  InstructionCode opcode = value_binop->rep.MapTaggedToWord() ==
3857  RegisterRepresentation::Word32()
3858  ? kArm64TestAndBranch32
3859  : kArm64TestAndBranch;
3860  Arm64OperandGenerator gen(this);
3861  EmitWithContinuation(opcode, gen.UseRegister(value_binop->left()),
3862  gen.TempImmediate(matcher.bit()), cont);
3863  return;
3864  }
3865  }
3866  }
3867 
3868  if (CanCover(user, value)) {
3869  if (const ComparisonOp* comparison = value_op.TryCast<ComparisonOp>()) {
3870  switch (comparison->rep.MapTaggedToWord().value()) {
3871  case RegisterRepresentation::Word32():
3872  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(
3873  GetComparisonFlagCondition(*comparison));
3874  return VisitWord32Compare(this, value, cont);
3875 
3876  case RegisterRepresentation::Word64():
3877  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(
3878  GetComparisonFlagCondition(*comparison));
3879 
3880  if (comparison->kind == ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual) {
3881  const Operation& left_op = Get(comparison->left());
3882  if (MatchIntegralZero(comparison->right()) &&
3883  left_op.Is<Opmask::kWord64BitwiseAnd>() &&
3884  CanCover(value, comparison->left())) {
3885  return VisitWordCompare(this, comparison->left(), kArm64Tst, cont,
3886  kLogical64Imm);
3887  }
3888  }
3889  return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kArm64Cmp, cont, kArithmeticImm);
3890 
3891  case RegisterRepresentation::Float32():
3892  switch (comparison->kind) {
3893  case ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual:
3894  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
3895  return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
3896  case ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan:
3897  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kFloatLessThan);
3898  return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
3899  case ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual:
3900  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kFloatLessThanOrEqual);
3901  return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
3902  default:
3903  UNREACHABLE();
3904  }
3905 
3906  case RegisterRepresentation::Float64():
3907  switch (comparison->kind) {
3908  case ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual:
3909  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
3910  return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
3911  case ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan:
3912  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kFloatLessThan);
3913  return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
3914  case ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual:
3915  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kFloatLessThanOrEqual);
3916  return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
3917  default:
3918  UNREACHABLE();
3919  }
3920 
3921  default:
3922  break;
3923  }
3924  } else if (const ProjectionOp* projection =
3925  value_op.TryCast<ProjectionOp>()) {
3926  // Check if this is the overflow output projection of an
3927  // <Operation>WithOverflow node.
3928  if (projection->index == 1u) {
3929  // We cannot combine the <Operation>WithOverflow with this branch
3930  // unless the 0th projection (the use of the actual value of the
3931  // <Operation> is either nullptr, which means there's no use of the
3932  // actual value, or was already defined, which means it is scheduled
3933  // *AFTER* this branch).
3934  OpIndex node = projection->input();
3935  if (const OverflowCheckedBinopOp* binop =
3936  TryCast<OverflowCheckedBinopOp>(node);
3937  binop && CanDoBranchIfOverflowFusion(node)) {
3938  const bool is64 = binop->rep == WordRepresentation::Word64();
3939  switch (binop->kind) {
3940  case OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedAdd:
3941  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
3942  return VisitBinop(this, node, binop->rep,
3943  is64 ? kArm64Add : kArm64Add32, kArithmeticImm,
3944  cont);
3945  case OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedSub:
3946  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
3947  return VisitBinop(this, node, binop->rep,
3948  is64 ? kArm64Sub : kArm64Sub32, kArithmeticImm,
3949  cont);
3950  case OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedMul:
3951  if (is64) {
3952  // ARM64 doesn't set the overflow flag for multiplication, so
3953  // we need to test on kNotEqual. Here is the code sequence
3954  // used:
3955  // mul result, left, right
3956  // smulh high, left, right
3957  // cmp high, result, asr 63
3958  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kNotEqual);
3959  return EmitInt64MulWithOverflow(this, node, cont);
3960  } else {
3961  // ARM64 doesn't set the overflow flag for multiplication, so
3962  // we need to test on kNotEqual. Here is the code sequence
3963  // used:
3964  // smull result, left, right
3965  // cmp result.X(), Operand(result, SXTW)
3966  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kNotEqual);
3967  return EmitInt32MulWithOverflow(this, node, cont);
3968  }
3969  }
3970  }
3971  }
3972  } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32Add>()) {
3973  return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kArm64Cmn32, cont, kArithmeticImm);
3974  } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32Sub>()) {
3975  return VisitWord32Compare(this, value, cont);
3976  } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>()) {
3977  if (TryMatchConditionalCompareChainBranch(this, zone(), value, cont)) {
3978  return;
3979  }
3980  return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kArm64Tst32, cont, kLogical32Imm);
3981  } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord64BitwiseAnd>()) {
3982  return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kArm64Tst, cont, kLogical64Imm);
3983  } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseOr>()) {
3984  if (TryMatchConditionalCompareChainBranch(this, zone(), value, cont)) {
3985  return;
3986  }
3987  } else if (value_op.Is<StackPointerGreaterThanOp>()) {
3988  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kStackPointerGreaterThanCondition);
3989  return VisitStackPointerGreaterThan(value, cont);
3990  }
3991  }
3992 
3993  // Branch could not be combined with a compare, compare against 0 and
3994  // branch.
3995  if (cont->IsBranch()) {
3996  Emit(cont->Encode(kArm64CompareAndBranch32), g.NoOutput(),
3997  g.UseRegister(value), g.Label(cont->true_block()),
3998  g.Label(cont->false_block()));
3999  } else {
4000  VisitCompare(this, cont->Encode(kArm64Tst32), g.UseRegister(value),
4001  g.UseRegister(value), cont);
4002  }
4003 }
4004 
4005 void InstructionSelector::VisitSwitch(OpIndex node, const SwitchInfo& sw) {
4006  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
4007  const SwitchOp& op = Cast<SwitchOp>(node);
4008  InstructionOperand value_operand = g.UseRegister(op.input());
4009 
4010  // Emit either ArchTableSwitch or ArchBinarySearchSwitch.
4011  if (enable_switch_jump_table_) {
4012  static const size_t kMaxTableSwitchValueRange = 2 << 16;
4013  size_t table_space_cost = 4 + sw.value_range();
4014  size_t table_time_cost = 3;
4015  size_t lookup_space_cost = 3 + 2 * sw.case_count();
4016  size_t lookup_time_cost = sw.case_count();
4017  if (sw.case_count() > 4 &&
4018  table_space_cost + 3 * table_time_cost <=
4019  lookup_space_cost + 3 * lookup_time_cost &&
4020  sw.min_value() > std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min() &&
4021  sw.value_range() <= kMaxTableSwitchValueRange) {
4022  InstructionOperand index_operand = value_operand;
4023  if (sw.min_value()) {
4024  index_operand = g.TempRegister();
4025  Emit(kArm64Sub32, index_operand, value_operand,
4026  g.TempImmediate(sw.min_value()));
4027  } else {
4028  // Smis top bits are undefined, so zero-extend if not already done so.
4029  if (!ZeroExtendsWord32ToWord64(op.input())) {
4030  index_operand = g.TempRegister();
4031  Emit(kArm64Mov32, index_operand, value_operand);
4032  }
4033  }
4034  // Generate a table lookup.
4035  return EmitTableSwitch(sw, index_operand);
4036  }
4037  }
4038 
4039  // Generate a tree of conditional jumps.
4040  return EmitBinarySearchSwitch(sw, value_operand);
4041 }
4042 
4043 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord32Equal(OpIndex node) {
4044  const Operation& equal = Get(node);
4045  DCHECK(equal.Is<ComparisonOp>());
4046  OpIndex left = equal.input(0);
4047  OpIndex right = equal.input(1);
4048  OpIndex user = node;
4049  FlagsContinuation cont = FlagsContinuation::ForSet(kEqual, node);
4050 
4051  if (MatchZero(right)) {
4052  OpIndex value = left;
4053  if (CanCover(user, value)) {
4054  const Operation& value_op = Get(value);
4055  if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32Add>() ||
4056  value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>()) {
4057  return VisitWord32Compare(this, node, &cont);
4058  }
4059  if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32Sub>()) {
4060  return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kArm64Cmp32, &cont,
4061  kArithmeticImm);
4062  }
4063  if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32Equal>()) {
4064  // Word32Equal(Word32Equal(x, y), 0) => Word32Compare(x, y, ne).
4065  // A new FlagsContinuation is needed as instead of generating the result
4066  // for {node}, it is generated for {value}.
4067  FlagsContinuation cont = FlagsContinuation::ForSet(kEqual, value);
4068  cont.Negate();
4069  VisitWord32Compare(this, value, &cont);
4070  EmitIdentity(node);
4071  return;
4072  }
4073  return VisitWord32Test(this, value, &cont);
4074  }
4075  }
4076 
4077  if (isolate() && (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL ||
4078  (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL && !isolate()->bootstrapper()))) {
4079  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
4080  const RootsTable& roots_table = isolate()->roots_table();
4081  RootIndex root_index;
4082  Handle<HeapObject> right;
4083  // HeapConstants and CompressedHeapConstants can be treated the same when
4084  // using them as an input to a 32-bit comparison. Check whether either is
4085  // present.
4086  if (MatchHeapConstant(node, &right) && !right.is_null() &&
4087  roots_table.IsRootHandle(right, &root_index)) {
4088  if (RootsTable::IsReadOnly(root_index)) {
4089  Tagged_t ptr =
4090  MacroAssemblerBase::ReadOnlyRootPtr(root_index, isolate());
4091  if (g.CanBeImmediate(ptr, ImmediateMode::kArithmeticImm)) {
4092  return VisitCompare(this, kArm64Cmp32, g.UseRegister(left),
4093  g.TempImmediate(ptr), &cont);
4094  }
4095  }
4096  }
4097  }
4098  VisitWord32Compare(this, node, &cont);
4099 }

4123 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord64Equal(OpIndex node) {
4124  FlagsContinuation cont = FlagsContinuation::ForSet(kEqual, node);
4125  const ComparisonOp& equal = this->Get(node).template Cast<ComparisonOp>();
4126  DCHECK_EQ(equal.kind, ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual);
4127  if (this->MatchIntegralZero(equal.right()) && CanCover(node, equal.left())) {
4128  if (this->Get(equal.left()).template Is<Opmask::kWord64BitwiseAnd>()) {
4129  return VisitWordCompare(this, equal.left(), kArm64Tst, &cont,
4130  kLogical64Imm);
4131  }
4132  return VisitWord64Test(this, equal.left(), &cont);
4133  }
4134  VisitWordCompare(this, node, kArm64Cmp, &cont, kArithmeticImm);
4135 }

4236 void InstructionSelector::VisitFloat32Neg(OpIndex node) {
4237  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
4238  OpIndex input = this->Get(node).input(0);
4239  const Operation& input_op = this->Get(input);
4240  if (input_op.Is<Opmask::kFloat32Mul>() && CanCover(node, input)) {
4241  const FloatBinopOp& mul = input_op.Cast<FloatBinopOp>();
4242  Emit(kArm64Float32Fnmul, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
4243  g.UseRegister(mul.left()), g.UseRegister(mul.right()));
4244  return;
4245  }
4246  VisitRR(this, kArm64Float32Neg, node);
4247 }

4252  const Operation& lhs = this->Get(mul.left());
4253 
4254  if (lhs.Is<Opmask::kFloat32Negate>() && CanCover(node, mul.left())) {
4255  Emit(kArm64Float32Fnmul, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
4256  g.UseRegister(lhs.input(0)), g.UseRegister(mul.right()));
4257  return;
4258  }

4260  const Operation& rhs = this->Get(mul.right());
4261  if (rhs.Is<Opmask::kFloat32Negate>() && CanCover(node, mul.right())) {
4262  Emit(kArm64Float32Fnmul, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
4263  g.UseRegister(rhs.input(0)), g.UseRegister(mul.left()));

4329 void InstructionSelector::VisitBitcastWord32PairToFloat64(OpIndex node) {
4330  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
4331  const auto& bitcast = this->Cast<BitcastWord32PairToFloat64Op>(node);
4332  OpIndex hi = bitcast.high_word32();
4333  OpIndex lo = bitcast.low_word32();
4334 
4335  int vreg = g.AllocateVirtualRegister();
4336  Emit(kArm64Bfi, g.DefineSameAsFirstForVreg(vreg), g.UseRegister(lo),
4337  g.UseRegister(hi), g.TempImmediate(32), g.TempImmediate(32));
4338  Emit(kArm64Float64MoveU64, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
4339  g.UseRegisterForVreg(vreg));
4340 }

4350 void InstructionSelector::VisitFloat64Neg(OpIndex node) {
4351  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
4352  OpIndex input = this->Get(node).input(0);
4353  const Operation& input_op = this->Get(input);
4354  if (input_op.Is<Opmask::kFloat64Mul>() && CanCover(node, input)) {
4355  const FloatBinopOp& mul = input_op.Cast<FloatBinopOp>();
4356  Emit(kArm64Float64Fnmul, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
4357  g.UseRegister(mul.left()), g.UseRegister(mul.right()));
4358  return;
4359  }
4360  VisitRR(this, kArm64Float64Neg, node);
4361 }
4362 
4363 void InstructionSelector::VisitFloat64Mul(OpIndex node) {
4364  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
4365  const FloatBinopOp& mul = this->Get(node).template Cast<FloatBinopOp>();
4366  const Operation& lhs = this->Get(mul.left());
4367  if (lhs.Is<Opmask::kFloat64Negate>() && CanCover(node, mul.left())) {
4368  Emit(kArm64Float64Fnmul, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
4369  g.UseRegister(lhs.input(0)), g.UseRegister(mul.right()));
4370  return;
4371  }
4372 
4373  const Operation& rhs = this->Get(mul.right());
4374  if (rhs.Is<Opmask::kFloat64Negate>() && CanCover(node, mul.right())) {
4375  Emit(kArm64Float64Fnmul, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
4376  g.UseRegister(rhs.input(0)), g.UseRegister(mul.left()));
4377  return;
4378  }
4379  return VisitRRR(this, kArm64Float64Mul, node);
4380 }

4382 void InstructionSelector::VisitMemoryBarrier(OpIndex node) {
4383  // Use DMB ISH for both acquire-release and sequentially consistent barriers.
4384  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
4385  Emit(kArm64DmbIsh, g.NoOutput());
4386 }

4404 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord32AtomicExchange(OpIndex node) {
4405  const AtomicRMWOp& atomic_op = this->Get(node).template Cast<AtomicRMWOp>();
4406  ArchOpcode opcode;
4407  if (atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Int8()) {
4408  opcode = kAtomicExchangeInt8;
4409  } else if (atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Uint8()) {
4410  opcode = kAtomicExchangeUint8;
4411  } else if (atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Int16()) {
4412  opcode = kAtomicExchangeInt16;
4413  } else if (atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Uint16()) {
4414  opcode = kAtomicExchangeUint16;
4415  } else if (atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Int32() ||
4416  atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Uint32()) {
4417  opcode = kAtomicExchangeWord32;
4418  } else {
4419  UNREACHABLE();
4420  }
4421  VisitAtomicExchange(this, node, opcode, AtomicWidth::kWord32,
4422  atomic_op.memory_access_kind);
4423 }

4704 void InstructionSelector::VisitS128Const(OpIndex node) {
4705  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
4706  static const int kUint32Immediates = 4;
4707  uint32_t val[kUint32Immediates];
4708  static_assert(sizeof(val) == kSimd128Size);
4709  const Simd128ConstantOp& constant =
4710  this->Get(node).template Cast<Simd128ConstantOp>();
4711  memcpy(val, constant.value, kSimd128Size);
4712  Emit(kArm64S128Const, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseImmediate(val[0]),
4713  g.UseImmediate(val[1]), g.UseImmediate(val[2]), g.UseImmediate(val[3]));
4714 }

4718 struct BicImmParam {
4719  BicImmParam(uint32_t imm, uint8_t lane_size, uint8_t shift_amount)
4720  : imm(imm), lane_size(lane_size), shift_amount(shift_amount) {}
4721  uint8_t imm;
4722  uint8_t lane_size;
4723  uint8_t shift_amount;
4724 };
4725 
4726 struct BicImmResult {
4727  BicImmResult(std::optional<BicImmParam> param, OpIndex const_node,
4728  OpIndex other_node)
4729  : param(param), const_node(const_node), other_node(other_node) {}
4730  std::optional<BicImmParam> param;
4731  OpIndex const_node;
4732  OpIndex other_node;
4733 };
4734 
4735 std::optional<BicImmParam> BicImm16bitHelper(uint16_t val) {
4736  uint8_t byte0 = val & 0xFF;
4737  uint8_t byte1 = val >> 8;
4738  // Cannot use Bic if both bytes are not 0x00
4739  if (byte0 == 0x00) {
4740  return BicImmParam(byte1, 16, 8);
4741  }
4742  if (byte1 == 0x00) {
4743  return BicImmParam(byte0, 16, 0);
4744  }
4745  return std::nullopt;
4746 }
4747 
4748 std::optional<BicImmParam> BicImm32bitHelper(uint32_t val) {
4749  for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
4750  // All bytes are 0 but one
4751  if ((val & (0xFF << (8 * i))) == val) {
4752  return BicImmParam(static_cast<uint8_t>(val >> i * 8), 32, i * 8);
4753  }
4754  }
4755  // Low and high 2 bytes are equal
4756  if ((val >> 16) == (0xFFFF & val)) {
4757  return BicImm16bitHelper(0xFFFF & val);
4758  }
4759  return std::nullopt;
4760 }
4761 
4762 std::optional<BicImmParam> BicImmConstHelper(const Operation& op,
4763  bool not_imm) {
4764  const int kUint32Immediates = 4;
4765  uint32_t val[kUint32Immediates];
4766  static_assert(sizeof(val) == kSimd128Size);
4767  memcpy(val, op.Cast<Simd128ConstantOp>().value, kSimd128Size);
4768  // If 4 uint32s are not the same, cannot emit Bic
4769  if (!(val[0] == val[1] && val[1] == val[2] && val[2] == val[3])) {
4770  return std::nullopt;
4771  }
4772  return BicImm32bitHelper(not_imm ? ~val[0] : val[0]);
4773 }
4774 
4775 std::optional<BicImmResult> BicImmHelper(InstructionSelector* selector,
4776  OpIndex and_node, bool not_imm) {
4777  const Simd128BinopOp& op = selector->Get(and_node).Cast<Simd128BinopOp>();
4778  // If we are negating the immediate then we are producing And(x, imm), and so
4779  // can take the immediate from the left or right input. Otherwise we are
4780  // producing And(x, Not(imm)), which can only be used when the immediate is
4781  // the right (negated) input.
4782  if (not_imm && selector->Get(op.left()).Is<Simd128ConstantOp>()) {
4783  return BicImmResult(BicImmConstHelper(selector->Get(op.left()), not_imm),
4784  op.left(), op.right());
4785  }
4786  if (selector->Get(op.right()).Is<Simd128ConstantOp>()) {
4787  return BicImmResult(BicImmConstHelper(selector->Get(op.right()), not_imm),
4788  op.right(), op.left());
4789  }
4790  return std::nullopt;
4791 }
4792 
4793 bool TryEmitS128AndNotImm(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
4794  bool not_imm) {
4795  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
4796  std::optional<BicImmResult> result = BicImmHelper(selector, node, not_imm);
4797  if (!result.has_value()) return false;
4798  std::optional<BicImmParam> param = result->param;
4799  if (param.has_value()) {
4800  if (selector->CanCover(node, result->other_node)) {
4801  selector->Emit(
4802  kArm64S128AndNot | LaneSizeField::encode(param->lane_size),
4803  g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(result->other_node),
4804  g.UseImmediate(param->imm), g.UseImmediate(param->shift_amount));
4805  return true;
4806  }
4807  }
4808  return false;
4809 }
4810 
4811 } // namespace

4813 void InstructionSelector::VisitS128AndNot(OpIndex node) {
4814  if (!TryEmitS128AndNotImm(this, node, false)) {
4815  VisitRRR(this, kArm64S128AndNot, node);
4816  }
4817 }

4821  if (!TryEmitS128AndNotImm(this, node, true)) {
4822  VisitRRR(this, kArm64S128And, node);
4823  }
4824 }

4829  g.UseImmediate(0), g.UseImmediate(0), g.UseImmediate(0));

4832 void InstructionSelector::VisitI32x4DotI8x16I7x16AddS(OpIndex node) {

4836  ? g.DefineSameAsInput(node, 2)
4837  : g.DefineAsRegister(node);

4928 using ShuffleMatcher =

4933 namespace {
4934 // Struct holding the result of pattern-matching a mul+dup.
4935 struct MulWithDup {
4936  OpIndex input; // Node holding the vector elements.
4937  OpIndex dup_node; // Node holding the lane to multiply.
4938  int index;
4939  // Pattern-match is successful if dup_node is set.
4940  explicit operator bool() const { return dup_node.valid(); }
4941 };
4942 
4943 template <int LANES>
4944 MulWithDup TryMatchMulWithDup(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node) {
4945  // Pattern match:
4946  // f32x4.mul(x, shuffle(x, y, indices)) => f32x4.mul(x, y, laneidx)
4947  // f64x2.mul(x, shuffle(x, y, indices)) => f64x2.mul(x, y, laneidx)
4948  // where shuffle(x, y, indices) = dup(x[laneidx]) or dup(y[laneidx])
4949  // f32x4.mul and f64x2.mul are commutative, so use BinopMatcher.
4950  OpIndex input;
4951  OpIndex dup_node;
4952 
4953  int index = 0;
4954 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4955  const Simd128BinopOp& mul = selector->Get(node).Cast<Simd128BinopOp>();
4956  const Operation& left = selector->Get(mul.left());
4957  const Operation& right = selector->Get(mul.right());
4958 
4959  // TODO(zhin): We can canonicalize first to avoid checking index < LANES.
4960  // e.g. shuffle(x, y, [16, 17, 18, 19...]) => shuffle(y, y, [0, 1, 2,
4961  // 3]...). But doing so can mutate the inputs of the shuffle node without
4962  // updating the shuffle immediates themselves. Fix that before we
4963  // canonicalize here. We don't want CanCover here because in many use cases,
4964  // the shuffle is generated early in the function, but the f32x4.mul happens
4965  // in a loop, which won't cover the shuffle since they are different basic
4966  // blocks.
4967  if (left.Is<Simd128ShuffleOp>() &&
4968  wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchSplat<LANES>(
4969  left.Cast<Simd128ShuffleOp>().shuffle, &index)) {
4970  dup_node = left.input(index < LANES ? 0 : 1);
4971  input = mul.right();
4972  } else if (right.Is<Simd128ShuffleOp>() &&
4973  wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchSplat<LANES>(
4974  right.Cast<Simd128ShuffleOp>().shuffle, &index)) {
4975  dup_node = right.input(index < LANES ? 0 : 1);
4976  input = mul.left();
4977  }
4978 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4979 
4980  // Canonicalization would get rid of this too.
4981  index %= LANES;
4982 
4983  return {input, dup_node, index};
4984 }
4985 } // namespace
4986 
4987 void InstructionSelector::VisitF16x8Mul(OpIndex node) {
4988  if (MulWithDup result = TryMatchMulWithDup<8>(this, node)) {
4989  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
4990  Emit(kArm64FMulElement | LaneSizeField::encode(16),
4991  g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(result.input),
4992  g.UseRegister(result.dup_node), g.UseImmediate(result.index));
4993  } else {
4994  return VisitRRR(this, kArm64FMul | LaneSizeField::encode(16), node);
4995  }
4996 }

5030 // Tries to match either input of a commutative binop to a given Opmask.
5031 class SimdBinopMatcherTurboshaft {
5032  public:
5033  SimdBinopMatcherTurboshaft(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node)
5034  : selector_(selector), node_(node) {
5035  const Simd128BinopOp& add_op = selector->Get(node).Cast<Simd128BinopOp>();
5036  DCHECK(Simd128BinopOp::IsCommutative(add_op.kind));
5037  input0_ = add_op.left();
5038  input1_ = add_op.right();
5039  }
5040  template <typename OpmaskT>
5041  bool InputMatches() {
5042  if (selector_->Get(input1_).Is<OpmaskT>()) {
5043  std::swap(input0_, input1_);
5044  return true;
5045  }
5046  return selector_->Get(input0_).Is<OpmaskT>();
5047  }
5048  OpIndex matched_input() const { return input0_; }
5049  OpIndex other_input() const { return input1_; }
5050 
5051  private:
5052  InstructionSelector* selector_;
5053  OpIndex node_;
5054  OpIndex input0_;
5055  OpIndex input1_;
5056 };
5057 
5058 template <typename OpmaskT>
5059 bool ShraHelper(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node, int lane_size,
5060  InstructionCode shra_code, InstructionCode add_code) {
5061  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
5062  SimdBinopMatcherTurboshaft m(selector, node);
5063  if (!m.InputMatches<OpmaskT>() ||
5064  !selector->CanCover(node, m.matched_input())) {
5065  return false;
5066  }
5067  const Simd128ShiftOp& shiftop =
5068  selector->Get(m.matched_input()).Cast<Simd128ShiftOp>();
5069  int64_t constant;
5070  if (!selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(shiftop.shift(), &constant)) {
5071  return false;
5072  }
5073 
5074  // If shifting by zero, just do the addition
5075  if (constant % lane_size == 0) {
5076  selector->Emit(add_code, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
5077  g.UseRegister(shiftop.input()),
5078  g.UseRegister(m.other_input()));
5079  } else {
5080  selector->Emit(shra_code | LaneSizeField::encode(lane_size),
5081  g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(m.other_input()),
5082  g.UseRegister(shiftop.input()),
5083  g.UseImmediate(shiftop.shift()));
5084  }
5085  return true;
5086 }
5087 
5088 template <typename OpmaskT>
5089 bool AdalpHelper(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node, int lane_size,
5090  InstructionCode adalp_code) {
5091  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
5092  SimdBinopMatcherTurboshaft m(selector, node);
5093  if (!m.InputMatches<OpmaskT>() ||
5094  !selector->CanCover(node, m.matched_input())) {
5095  return false;
5096  }
5097  selector->Emit(adalp_code | LaneSizeField::encode(lane_size),
5098  g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(m.other_input()),
5099  g.UseRegister(selector->Get(m.matched_input()).input(0)));
5100  return true;
5101 }
5102 
5103 template <typename OpmaskT>
5104 bool MlaHelper(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
5105  InstructionCode mla_code) {
5106  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
5107  SimdBinopMatcherTurboshaft m(selector, node);
5108  if (!m.InputMatches<OpmaskT>() ||
5109  !selector->CanCover(node, m.matched_input())) {
5110  return false;
5111  }
5112  const Operation& mul = selector->Get(m.matched_input());
5113  selector->Emit(mla_code, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node),
5114  g.UseRegister(m.other_input()), g.UseRegister(mul.input(0)),
5115  g.UseRegister(mul.input(1)));
5116  return true;
5117 }
5118 
5119 template <Simd128BinopOp::Kind kind>
5120 bool SmlalHelper(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node, int lane_size,
5121  InstructionCode smlal_code) {
5122  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
5123  SimdBinopMatcherTurboshaft m(selector, node);
5124  using OpmaskT = Opmask::Simd128BinopMask::For<kind>;
5125  if (!m.InputMatches<OpmaskT>() ||
5126  !selector->CanCover(node, m.matched_input()))
5127  return false;
5128 
5129  const Operation& matched = selector->Get(m.matched_input());
5130  selector->Emit(smlal_code | LaneSizeField::encode(lane_size),
5131  g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(m.other_input()),
5132  g.UseRegister(matched.input(0)),
5133  g.UseRegister(matched.input(1)));
5134  return true;
5135 }

5137 template <typename OpmaskT>
5138 bool sha3helper(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
5139  InstructionCode sha3_code) {
5140  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
5141  SimdBinopMatcherTurboshaft m(selector, node);
5142  if (!m.InputMatches<OpmaskT>() ||
5143  !selector->CanCover(node, m.matched_input())) {
5144  return false;
5145  }
5146  const Operation& matched = selector->Get(m.matched_input());
5147  selector->Emit(
5148  sha3_code, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(m.other_input()),
5149  g.UseRegister(matched.input(0)), g.UseRegister(matched.input(1)));
5150  return true;
5151 }

5155 void InstructionSelector::VisitS128Xor(OpIndex node) {
5156  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
5157 
5158  if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SHA3)) {
5159  return VisitRRR(this, kArm64S128Xor, node);
5160  }
5161 
5162  if (sha3helper<Opmask::kSimd128AndNot>(this, node, kArm64Bcax) ||
5163  sha3helper<Opmask::kSimd128Xor>(this, node, kArm64Eor3))
5164  return;
5165 
5166  return VisitRRR(this, kArm64S128Xor, node);
5167 }
