5188 #define VISIT_SIMD_ADD(Type, PairwiseType, LaneSize) \
5189  void InstructionSelector::Visit##Type##Add(OpIndex node) { \
5190  /* Select Mla(z, x, y) for Add(x, Mul(y, z)). */ \
5191  if (MlaHelper<Opmask::kSimd128##Type##Mul>( \
5192  this, node, kArm64Mla | LaneSizeField::encode(LaneSize))) { \
5193  return; \
5194  } \
5195  /* Select S/Uadalp(x, y) for Add(x, ExtAddPairwise(y)). */ \
5196  if (AdalpHelper<Opmask::kSimd128##Type##ExtAddPairwise##PairwiseType##S>( \
5197  this, node, LaneSize, kArm64Sadalp) || \
5198  AdalpHelper<Opmask::kSimd128##Type##ExtAddPairwise##PairwiseType##U>( \
5199  this, node, LaneSize, kArm64Uadalp)) { \
5200  return; \
5201  } \
5202  /* Select S/Usra(x, y) for Add(x, ShiftRight(y, imm)). */ \
5203  if (ShraHelper<Opmask::kSimd128##Type##ShrS>( \
5204  this, node, LaneSize, kArm64Ssra, \
5205  kArm64IAdd | LaneSizeField::encode(LaneSize)) || \
5206  ShraHelper<Opmask::kSimd128##Type##ShrU>( \
5207  this, node, LaneSize, kArm64Usra, \
5208  kArm64IAdd | LaneSizeField::encode(LaneSize))) { \
5209  return; \
5210  } \
5211  /* Select Smlal/Umlal(x, y, z) for Add(x, ExtMulLow(y, z)) and \
5212  * Smlal2/Umlal2(x, y, z) for Add(x, ExtMulHigh(y, z)). */ \
5213  if (SmlalHelper< \
5214  Simd128BinopOp::Kind::k##Type##ExtMulLow##PairwiseType##S>( \
5215  this, node, LaneSize, kArm64Smlal) || \
5216  SmlalHelper< \
5217  Simd128BinopOp::Kind::k##Type##ExtMulHigh##PairwiseType##S>( \
5218  this, node, LaneSize, kArm64Smlal2) || \
5219  SmlalHelper< \
5220  Simd128BinopOp::Kind::k##Type##ExtMulLow##PairwiseType##U>( \
5221  this, node, LaneSize, kArm64Umlal) || \
5222  SmlalHelper< \
5223  Simd128BinopOp::Kind::k##Type##ExtMulHigh##PairwiseType##U>( \
5224  this, node, LaneSize, kArm64Umlal2)) { \
5225  return; \
5226  } \
5227  VisitRRR(this, kArm64IAdd | LaneSizeField::encode(LaneSize), node); \
5228  }
5229 
5230 VISIT_SIMD_ADD(I32x4, I16x8, 32)
5231 VISIT_SIMD_ADD(I16x8, I8x16, 16)
5232 #undef VISIT_SIMD_ADD

5234 #define VISIT_SIMD_SUB(Type, LaneSize) \
5235  void InstructionSelector::Visit##Type##Sub(OpIndex node) { \
5236  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this); \
5237  const Simd128BinopOp& sub = Get(node).Cast<Simd128BinopOp>(); \
5238  const Operation& right = Get(sub.right()); \
5239  /* Select Mls(z, x, y) for Sub(z, Mul(x, y)). */ \
5240  if (right.Is<Opmask::kSimd128##Type##Mul>() && \
5241  CanCover(node, sub.right())) { \
5242  Emit(kArm64Mls | LaneSizeField::encode(LaneSize), \
5243  g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(sub.left()), \
5244  g.UseRegister(right.input(0)), g.UseRegister(right.input(1))); \
5245  return; \
5246  } \
5247  VisitRRR(this, kArm64ISub | LaneSizeField::encode(LaneSize), node); \
5248  }

5277 namespace {
5278 bool isSimdZero(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node) {
5279  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
5280  if (auto constant = op.TryCast<Simd128ConstantOp>()) {
5281  return constant->IsZero();
5282  }
5283  return false;
5284 }

5288 #define VISIT_SIMD_CM(Type, T, CmOp, CmOpposite, LaneSize) \
5289  void InstructionSelector::Visit##Type##CmOp(OpIndex node) { \
5290  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this); \
5291  const Simd128BinopOp& op = Cast<Simd128BinopOp>(node); \
5292  OpIndex left = op.left(); \
5293  OpIndex right = op.right(); \
5294  if (isSimdZero(this, left)) { \
5295  Emit(kArm64##T##CmOpposite | LaneSizeField::encode(LaneSize), \
5296  g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(right)); \
5297  return; \
5298  } else if (isSimdZero(this, right)) { \
5299  Emit(kArm64##T##CmOp | LaneSizeField::encode(LaneSize), \
5300  g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(left)); \
5301  return; \
5302  } \
5303  VisitRRR(this, kArm64##T##CmOp | LaneSizeField::encode(LaneSize), node); \
5304  }

5377 void ArrangeShuffleTable(Arm64OperandGenerator* g, OpIndex input0,
5378  OpIndex input1, InstructionOperand* src0,
5379  InstructionOperand* src1) {
5380  if (input0 == input1) {
5381  // Unary, any q-register can be the table.
5382  *src0 = *src1 = g->UseRegister(input0);
5383  } else {
5384  // Binary, table registers must be consecutive.
5385  *src0 = g->UseFixed(input0, fp_fixed1);
5386  *src1 = g->UseFixed(input1, fp_fixed2);
5387  }
5388 }
5389 
5390 using CanonicalShuffle = wasm::SimdShuffle::CanonicalShuffle;
5391 std::optional<ArchOpcode> TryMapCanonicalShuffleToArch(
5392  CanonicalShuffle shuffle) {
5393  using CanonicalToArch = std::pair<CanonicalShuffle, ArchOpcode>;
5394  constexpr static auto arch_shuffles = std::to_array<CanonicalToArch>({
5395  {CanonicalShuffle::kS64x2Even, kArm64S64x2UnzipLeft},
5396  {CanonicalShuffle::kS64x2Odd, kArm64S64x2UnzipRight},
5397  {CanonicalShuffle::kS64x2ReverseBytes, kArm64S8x8Reverse},
5398  {CanonicalShuffle::kS32x4Even, kArm64S32x4UnzipLeft},
5399  {CanonicalShuffle::kS32x4Odd, kArm64S32x4UnzipRight},
5400  {CanonicalShuffle::kS32x4InterleaveLowHalves, kArm64S32x4ZipLeft},
5401  {CanonicalShuffle::kS32x4InterleaveHighHalves, kArm64S32x4ZipRight},
5402  {CanonicalShuffle::kS32x4ReverseBytes, kArm64S8x4Reverse},
5403  {CanonicalShuffle::kS32x4Reverse, kArm64S32x4Reverse},
5404  {CanonicalShuffle::kS32x2Reverse, kArm64S32x2Reverse},
5405  {CanonicalShuffle::kS32x4TransposeEven, kArm64S32x4TransposeLeft},
5406  {CanonicalShuffle::kS32x4TransposeOdd, kArm64S32x4TransposeRight},
5407  {CanonicalShuffle::kS16x8Even, kArm64S16x8UnzipLeft},
5408  {CanonicalShuffle::kS16x8Odd, kArm64S16x8UnzipRight},
5409  {CanonicalShuffle::kS16x8InterleaveLowHalves, kArm64S16x8ZipLeft},
5410  {CanonicalShuffle::kS16x8InterleaveHighHalves, kArm64S16x8ZipRight},
5411  {CanonicalShuffle::kS16x2Reverse, kArm64S16x2Reverse},
5412  {CanonicalShuffle::kS16x4Reverse, kArm64S16x4Reverse},
5413  {CanonicalShuffle::kS16x8ReverseBytes, kArm64S8x2Reverse},
5414  {CanonicalShuffle::kS16x8TransposeEven, kArm64S16x8TransposeLeft},
5415  {CanonicalShuffle::kS16x8TransposeOdd, kArm64S16x8TransposeRight},
5416  {CanonicalShuffle::kS8x16Even, kArm64S8x16UnzipLeft},
5417  {CanonicalShuffle::kS8x16Odd, kArm64S8x16UnzipRight},
5418  {CanonicalShuffle::kS8x16InterleaveLowHalves, kArm64S8x16ZipLeft},
5419  {CanonicalShuffle::kS8x16InterleaveHighHalves, kArm64S8x16ZipRight},
5420  {CanonicalShuffle::kS8x16TransposeEven, kArm64S8x16TransposeLeft},
5421  {CanonicalShuffle::kS8x16TransposeOdd, kArm64S8x16TransposeRight},
5422  });
5423 
5424  for (auto& [canonical, arch_opcode] : arch_shuffles) {
5425  if (canonical == shuffle) {
5426  return arch_opcode;
5427  }
5428  }
5429  return {};
5430 }
5431 } // namespace

5433 void InstructionSelector::VisitI8x2Shuffle(OpIndex node) {
5434  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
5435  auto view = this->simd_shuffle_view(node);
5436  constexpr size_t shuffle_bytes = 2;
5437  OpIndex input0 = view.input(0);
5438  OpIndex input1 = view.input(1);
5439  std::array<uint8_t, shuffle_bytes> shuffle;
5440  std::copy(view.data(), view.data() + shuffle_bytes, shuffle.begin());
5441 
5442  uint8_t shuffle16x1;
5443  if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatch16x1Shuffle(shuffle.data(), &shuffle16x1)) {
5444  Emit(kArm64S16x1Shuffle, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
5445  g.UseRegister(input1), g.UseImmediate(shuffle16x1));
5446  } else {
5447  Emit(kArm64S8x2Shuffle, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
5448  g.UseRegister(input1),
5449  g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack2Lanes(shuffle)));
5450  }
5451 }
5452 
5453 void InstructionSelector::VisitI8x4Shuffle(OpIndex node) {
5454  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
5455  auto view = this->simd_shuffle_view(node);
5456  OpIndex input0 = view.input(0);
5457  OpIndex input1 = view.input(1);
5458  constexpr size_t shuffle_bytes = 4;
5459  std::array<uint8_t, shuffle_bytes> shuffle;
5460  std::copy(view.data(), view.data() + shuffle_bytes, shuffle.begin());
5461  std::array<uint8_t, 2> shuffle16x2;
5462  uint8_t shuffle32x1;
5463 
5464  if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatch32x1Shuffle(shuffle.data(), &shuffle32x1)) {
5465  Emit(kArm64S32x1Shuffle, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
5466  g.UseRegister(input1), g.UseImmediate(shuffle32x1));
5467  } else if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatch16x2Shuffle(shuffle.data(),
5468  shuffle16x2.data())) {
5469  Emit(kArm64S16x2Shuffle, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
5470  g.UseRegister(input1),
5471  g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack2Lanes(shuffle16x2)));
5472  } else {
5473  InstructionOperand src0, src1;
5474  ArrangeShuffleTable(&g, input0, input1, &src0, &src1);
5475  Emit(kArm64I8x16Shuffle, g.DefineAsRegister(node), src0, src1,
5476  g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(&shuffle[0])),
5477  g.UseImmediate(0), g.UseImmediate(0), g.UseImmediate(0));
5478  }
5479 }
5480 
5481 void InstructionSelector::VisitI8x8Shuffle(OpIndex node) {
5482  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
5483  auto view = this->simd_shuffle_view(node);
5484  OpIndex input0 = view.input(0);
5485  OpIndex input1 = view.input(1);
5486  constexpr size_t shuffle_bytes = 8;
5487  std::array<uint8_t, shuffle_bytes> shuffle;
5488  std::copy(view.data(), view.data() + shuffle_bytes, shuffle.begin());
5489  std::array<uint8_t, 2> shuffle32x2;
5490  uint8_t shuffle64x1;
5491  if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatch64x1Shuffle(shuffle.data(), &shuffle64x1)) {
5492  Emit(kArm64S64x1Shuffle, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
5493  g.UseRegister(input1), g.UseImmediate(shuffle64x1));
5494  } else if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatch32x2Shuffle(shuffle.data(),
5495  shuffle32x2.data())) {
5496  Emit(kArm64S32x2Shuffle, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
5497  g.UseRegister(input1),
5498  g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack2Lanes(shuffle32x2)));
5499  } else {
5500  // Code generator uses vtbl, arrange sources to form a valid lookup table.
5501  InstructionOperand src0, src1;
5502  ArrangeShuffleTable(&g, input0, input1, &src0, &src1);
5503  Emit(kArm64I8x16Shuffle, g.DefineAsRegister(node), src0, src1,
5504  g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(&shuffle[0])),
5505  g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(&shuffle[4])),
5506  g.UseImmediate(0), g.UseImmediate(0));
5507  }
5508 }
5509 
5510 void InstructionSelector::VisitI8x16Shuffle(OpIndex node) {
5511  std::array<uint8_t, kSimd128Size> shuffle;
5512  bool is_swizzle;
5513  auto view = this->simd_shuffle_view(node);
5514  CanonicalizeShuffle(view, shuffle.data(), &is_swizzle);
5515  OpIndex input0 = view.input(0);
5516  OpIndex input1 = view.input(1);
5517  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
5518 
5519  const CanonicalShuffle canonical =
5520  wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchCanonical(shuffle);
5521 
5522  if (auto arch_opcode = TryMapCanonicalShuffleToArch(canonical);
5523  arch_opcode.has_value()) {
5524  Emit(arch_opcode.value(), g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
5525  g.UseRegister(input1));
5526  return;
5527  }
5528 
5529  uint8_t offset;
5530  if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchConcat(shuffle.data(), &offset)) {
5531  Emit(kArm64S8x16Concat, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
5532  g.UseRegister(input1), g.UseImmediate(offset));
5533  return;
5534  }
5535  std::array<uint8_t, 2> shuffle64x2;
5536  if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatch64x2Shuffle(shuffle.data(),
5537  shuffle64x2.data())) {
5538  Emit(kArm64S64x2Shuffle, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
5539  g.UseRegister(input1),
5540  g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack2Lanes(shuffle64x2)));
5541  return;
5542  }
5543  uint8_t shuffle32x4[4];
5544  int index = 0;
5545  uint8_t from = 0;
5546  uint8_t to = 0;
5547  if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatch32x4Shuffle(shuffle.data(), shuffle32x4)) {
5548  if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchSplat<4>(shuffle.data(), &index)) {
5549  DCHECK_GT(4, index);
5550  Emit(kArm64S128Dup, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
5551  g.UseImmediate(4), g.UseImmediate(index % 4));
5552  } else if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatch32x4OneLaneSwizzle(shuffle32x4, &from,
5553  &to)) {
5554  Emit(kArm64S32x4OneLaneSwizzle, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
5555  g.UseRegister(input0), g.TempImmediate(from), g.TempImmediate(to));
5556  } else if (canonical == CanonicalShuffle::kIdentity) {
5557  // Bypass normal shuffle code generation in this case.
5558  // EmitIdentity
5559  MarkAsUsed(input0);
5560  MarkAsDefined(node);
5561  SetRename(node, input0);
5562  } else {
5563  Emit(kArm64S32x4Shuffle, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
5564  g.UseRegister(input1),
5565  g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(shuffle32x4)));
5566  }
5567  return;
5568  }
5569  if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchSplat<8>(shuffle.data(), &index)) {
5570  DCHECK_GT(8, index);
5571  Emit(kArm64S128Dup, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
5572  g.UseImmediate(8), g.UseImmediate(index % 8));
5573  return;
5574  }
5575  if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchSplat<16>(shuffle.data(), &index)) {
5576  DCHECK_GT(16, index);
5577  Emit(kArm64S128Dup, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
5578  g.UseImmediate(16), g.UseImmediate(index % 16));
5579  return;
5580  }
5581  // Code generator uses vtbl, arrange sources to form a valid lookup table.
5582  InstructionOperand src0, src1;
5583  ArrangeShuffleTable(&g, input0, input1, &src0, &src1);
5584  Emit(kArm64I8x16Shuffle, g.DefineAsRegister(node), src0, src1,
5585  g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(&shuffle[0])),
5586  g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(&shuffle[4])),
5587  g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(&shuffle[8])),
5588  g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(&shuffle[12])));
5589 }

5621 namespace {
5622 void VisitPminOrPmax(InstructionSelector* selector, ArchOpcode opcode,
5623  OpIndex node) {
5624  Arm64OperandGenerator g(selector);
5625  const Simd128BinopOp& op = selector->Cast<Simd128BinopOp>(node);
5626  // Need all unique registers because we first compare the two inputs, then
5627  // we need the inputs to remain unchanged for the bitselect later.
5628  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
5629  g.UseUniqueRegister(op.left()),
5630  g.UseUniqueRegister(op.right()));
5631 }
5632 } // namespace

5715 void InstructionSelector::VisitI8x16Popcnt(OpIndex node) {
5716  InstructionCode code = kArm64Cnt;
5717  code |= LaneSizeField::encode(8);
5718  VisitRR(this, code, node);
5719 }
5720 
5721 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_WASM_DEINTERLEAVED_MEM_OPS
5722 
5723 void InstructionSelector::VisitSimd128LoadPairDeinterleave(OpIndex node) {
5724  const auto& load = this->Get(node).Cast<Simd128LoadPairDeinterleaveOp>();
5725  Arm64OperandGenerator g(this);
5726  InstructionCode opcode = kArm64S128LoadPairDeinterleave;
5727  opcode |= LaneSizeField::encode(load.lane_size());
5728  if (load.load_kind.with_trap_handler) {
5729  opcode |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
5730  }
5731  OptionalOpIndex first = FindProjection(node, 0);
5732  OptionalOpIndex second = FindProjection(node, 1);
5733 
5734  InstructionOperand outputs[] = {
5735  g.DefineAsFixed(first.value(), fp_fixed1),
5736  g.DefineAsFixed(second.value(), fp_fixed2),
5737  };
5738 
5739  InstructionOperand inputs[] = {
5740  EmitAddBeforeLoadOrStore(this, node, &opcode),
5741  g.TempImmediate(0),
5742  };
5743  Emit(opcode, arraysize(outputs), outputs, arraysize(inputs), inputs);
5744 }
5745 
5746 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WASM_DEINTERLEAVED_MEM_OPS
5747 
5748 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5749 
5750 void InstructionSelector::AddOutputToSelectContinuation(OperandGenerator* g,
5751  int first_input_index,
5752  OpIndex node) {
5753  continuation_outputs_.push_back(g->DefineAsRegister(node));
5754 }

5757 MachineOperatorBuilder::Flags
5758 InstructionSelector::SupportedMachineOperatorFlags() {
5759  auto flags = MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat32RoundDown |
5760  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat64RoundDown |
5761  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat32RoundUp |
5762  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat64RoundUp |
5763  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat32RoundTruncate |
5764  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat64RoundTruncate |
5765  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat64RoundTiesAway |
5766  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat32RoundTiesEven |
5767  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat64RoundTiesEven |
5768  MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord32Popcnt |
5769  MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord64Popcnt |
5770  MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord32ShiftIsSafe |
5771  MachineOperatorBuilder::kInt32DivIsSafe |
5772  MachineOperatorBuilder::kUint32DivIsSafe |
5773  MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord32ReverseBits |
5774  MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord64ReverseBits |
5775  MachineOperatorBuilder::kSatConversionIsSafe |
5776  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat32Select |
5777  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat64Select |
5778  MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord32Select |
5779  MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord64Select |
5780  MachineOperatorBuilder::kLoadStorePairs;
5781  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(FP16)) {
5782  flags |= MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat16 |
5783  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat16RawBitsConversion;
5784  }
5785  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(CSSC)) {
5786  flags |=
5787  MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord32Ctz | MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord64Ctz;
5788  }
5789  return flags;
5790 }

5796  FullUnalignedAccessSupport();
